WEBVTT

00:23.023 --> 00:25.059
[ Liquid Dripping ]

00:27.828 --> 00:30.864
[ Man ] YOU'RE GONNA ACTUALLY
DRIVE THIS DEATHTRAP
FROM TENNESSEE TO CALIFORNIA?

00:30.931 --> 00:34.068
YOU'RE SAYIN' I'M NOT?
I'M SAYIN' YOU WON'T
MAKE IT PAST THAT TREE.

00:34.135 --> 00:38.639
HEY, NOVALEE, YOU PLANNIN'
ON LEAVIN' TODAY?
IN THE BATHROOM, WILLY JACK.

00:38.706 --> 00:40.774
WHY DON'T SHE JUST MOVE IN
TO THE DAMN BATHROOM?

00:40.841 --> 00:43.677
GET ALL THOSE PICTURES
AND KNICKKNACKS.
I'M READY.

00:43.744 --> 00:46.680
I'M READY TO GO.
NOW, HOLD ON, HOLD ON.

00:46.747 --> 00:49.283
NOW I GOTTA GO.

00:49.350 --> 00:53.954
- WE'LL MISS YOU, NOVALEE.
- YOU KNOW THE FLOOR'S MISSIN'.

00:54.021 --> 00:57.525
WILLY JACK GOT
THE WHOLE CAR FOR 80 BUCKS.
HE HAD TO FIX EVERYTHING ON IT.

00:57.591 --> 01:03.364
AND HERE'S THE BEST PART.
NO FIVES.

01:03.431 --> 01:05.899
YOU AND YOUR FIVES.
WHAT FIVES?

01:05.966 --> 01:11.505
ON MY FIFTH BIRTHDAY, MY MAMA
RAN OFF WITH A BASEBALL UMPIRE
NAMED FRED AND NEVER CAME BACK.

01:11.572 --> 01:14.675
AFTER I DROPPED OUT OF SCHOOL
AND WAS WAITIN' TABLES AT RED'S,

01:14.742 --> 01:16.944
ONE OF THE REGULARS THERE
NAMED GLADYS WENT CRAZY.

01:17.010 --> 01:19.613
WHEN I TRIED TO CALM HER DOWN
SHE JUMPED AT ME
WITH A STEAK KNIFE...

01:19.680 --> 01:22.550
AND CUT ME FROM MY WRIST
TO MY ELBOW.

01:22.616 --> 01:25.085
AND WHAT'S THAT
GOT TO DO WITH FIVES?

01:25.153 --> 01:27.155
IT TOOK 55 STITCHES
TO CLOSE HER UP.

01:27.221 --> 01:29.290
I DON'T LIKE FIVES.

01:32.693 --> 01:36.430
- THAT'S IT. LET'S HIT IT.
LET'S GO, LET'S GO!
- HON,

01:38.599 --> 01:41.369
WILL YOU TAKE A PICTURE OF US
WITH MY NEW CAMERA?

01:44.805 --> 01:49.777
- WAIT!
- ALL AROUND, LET'S GO.
COME ON, COME ON!

01:49.843 --> 01:53.414
I'M GONNA MISS YOU.
CALL ME, OKAY?
ALL RIGHT. BYE.

01:55.949 --> 01:58.252
ALL RIGHT. BYE.

01:58.319 --> 02:00.854
JESUS, FINALLY.
IT'S ALREADY 5:00.
5:00?

02:27.915 --> 02:31.485
I HOPE WE CAN A PLACE TO LIVE
THAT OVERLOOKS THE OCEAN.

02:31.552 --> 02:34.988
HELL, NOVALEE,
YOU CAN'T SEE THE OCEAN
FROM BAKERSFIELD.

02:35.055 --> 02:38.192
WELL-- WELL,
MAYBE A POND THEN.

02:38.259 --> 02:41.161
I WANNA GET
ONE OF THOSE PATIO TABLES
WITH AN UMBRELLA OVER IT...

02:41.229 --> 02:45.599
WHERE WE CAN SIT WITH THE BABY
AND DRINK CHOCOLATE MILK
AND WATCH THE SUN GO DOWN.

02:47.601 --> 02:50.471
I'VE NEVER LIVED
ANYPLACE THAT DIDN'T HAVE
WHEELS UNDER IT.

02:51.539 --> 02:54.775
HEY. HEY!
[ Whistles ]

02:58.312 --> 03:01.949
** [ Radio: Rock ]

03:02.015 --> 03:04.985
[ Willy Jack Singing ]
* SOMETIMES I WONDER *

03:05.052 --> 03:07.855
* WILL I EVER MAKE IT HOME *

03:10.491 --> 03:14.228
[ Snoring ]
* SOMETIMES I WONDER *

03:14.295 --> 03:16.997
* WILL I EVER MAKE IT HOME *

03:17.064 --> 03:18.899
[ Continues Snoring ]

03:20.468 --> 03:23.371
* I BEEN GONE SO LONG **
HEY!

03:25.839 --> 03:29.743
HEY, NOVALEE, WAKE UP!
YOU SOUND LIKE A DAMN PIG.

03:31.879 --> 03:35.215
JESUS. WHAT THE HELL'S
THE MATTER WITH YOU?

03:36.417 --> 03:38.652
AND WHERE ARE YOUR SHOES?

03:46.360 --> 03:48.462
THAT'S JUST GREAT.
THAT'S GREAT.

03:49.597 --> 03:52.566
MY FEET ARE SWOLLEN.
I HAD TO TAKE 'EM OFF.

03:54.302 --> 03:57.305
OOH!

03:57.371 --> 03:59.573
WANNA FEEL THE BABY?

04:00.874 --> 04:02.710
HERE.

04:04.111 --> 04:06.980
FEEL THAT?
NO.

04:09.717 --> 04:13.521
RIGHT THERE. FEEL THAT
LITTLE BOMP-BOMP-BOMP?

04:14.622 --> 04:16.624
THAT'S WHERE THE HEART IS.

04:19.959 --> 04:22.630
COULDN'T PROVE IT BY ME.

04:28.636 --> 04:31.372
- OOH!
- WOULD YA-- THE HELL--

04:31.439 --> 04:34.174
WAL-MART.
I CAN GO TO THE BATHROOM.

04:34.241 --> 04:37.545
[ Horns Honking ]

04:43.116 --> 04:47.287
ALL RIGHT. HURRY UP.
HON, I'M GONNA NEED
SOME MONEY.

04:47.355 --> 04:51.559
THEY GONNA CHARGE YOU TO PEE?
I HAVE TO GET SOME HOUSE SHOES.

04:51.625 --> 04:54.428
I GOTTA GET
SOME KIND OF SHOES.

04:57.498 --> 05:00.334
ALL RIGHT.
GET YOU SOME HOUSE SHOES.
COME ON.

05:00.401 --> 05:03.337
GET YOU SOME GREEN
POLKY-DOT HOUSE SHOES.

05:04.672 --> 05:07.475
THAT WAY EVERYONE WILL BE
SURE TO NOTICE YOU.

05:12.580 --> 05:14.548
[ Man Over Loudspeaker,
Indistinct ]

05:14.615 --> 05:16.950
BATHROOM, BATHROOM?
ALL THE WAY TO THE BACK.

05:17.017 --> 05:18.919
THANK YOU.

05:21.321 --> 05:25.459
YOU ALL GOT YOURSELF
A BEAUTIFUL CHILD HERE.
BE AN AWARD-WINNING PICTURE.

05:25.526 --> 05:29.530
I WOULDN'T BE SURPRISED
IF IT ENDS UP ON A CEREAL BOX.
STEVE, LOOK AT ME.

05:29.597 --> 05:32.400
SAY "CHEESE" FOR ME.
CHEESE.

05:36.937 --> 05:40.474
** [ Humming ]

05:41.442 --> 05:43.477
[ Woman ]
DO YOU MIND?

05:49.417 --> 05:51.685
[ Toilet Flushes ]

05:53.621 --> 05:55.623
** [ Continues Humming ]

05:59.393 --> 06:01.595
THANK YOU.

06:05.165 --> 06:06.967
[ Novalee Sighs Loudly ]

06:10.270 --> 06:12.840
[ Sighs Ecstatically ]
MOMMY!

06:14.742 --> 06:16.777
[ Register Beeping ]

06:21.715 --> 06:25.152
MA'AM, HERE'S YOUR CHANGE.
HMM? OH, SORRY.

06:25.218 --> 06:27.855
FIVE DOLLARS AND 55 CENTS.

06:29.022 --> 06:33.527
NO!
MA'AM!

06:35.328 --> 06:37.765
[ Whimpering ]

07:09.362 --> 07:12.199
MA'AM? MA'AM?

07:13.667 --> 07:15.769
YOU LEFT THESE
AT THE COUNTER.

07:18.639 --> 07:20.674
AND YOUR CHANGE.

07:23.343 --> 07:26.847
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
UH-HUH.

07:28.181 --> 07:31.752
I... JUST--

07:31.819 --> 07:36.490
MY BOYFRIEND...
WENT TO GET THE CAR FIXED.

07:38.325 --> 07:40.728
HE'LL PICK ME UP.

07:40.794 --> 07:44.565
WELL, HAVE A NICE DAY.

08:22.636 --> 08:26.674
WELL, RUTH ANN MOTT.

08:26.740 --> 08:30.177
WHY, HONEY,
JUST LOOK AT YOU!
LITTLE RUTH ANN MOTT.

08:30.243 --> 08:33.780
HONEY, I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU
SINCE YOUR MAMA PASSED.
WHAT'S THAT-- 10, 11 YEARS?

08:33.847 --> 08:37.317
- I'M NOT--
- DON'T YOU REMEMBER ME?
I'M SISTER HUSBAND.

08:37.384 --> 08:42.923
OH, YOU REMEMBER ME.
YOU USED TO CALL ME "TELMA"
BECAUSE YOU COULDN'T SAY THELMA.

08:42.990 --> 08:46.493
[ Laughs ]
CAN YOU SAY "THELMA"?

08:46.560 --> 08:49.429
- THELMA.
- GOOD!

08:49.496 --> 08:54.001
OH, LORD, LOOK AT YOU--
HAVIN' A BABY.

08:54.067 --> 08:57.170
SO, YOU JUST MOVE
BACK HOME, RUTH ANN?
SEE, I'M NOT WHO--

08:57.237 --> 09:00.674
OH, YOU KNOW WHAT THEY SAY:
"HOME IS WHERE
YOUR HISTORY BEGINS.

09:00.741 --> 09:04.978
HOME IS WHERE THEY CATCH YOU
WHEN YOU FALL."

09:05.045 --> 09:06.980
THAT'S WHAT THE LATE
BROTHER HUSBAND USED TO SAY.

09:07.047 --> 09:10.017
BROTHER HUSBAND--
WAS HE YOUR HUSBAND?

09:10.083 --> 09:14.221
NO, HE WAS MY BROTHER,
A REAL MAN OF GOD.

09:14.287 --> 09:18.692
- YOU READ THE BIBLE, RUTHIE?
- NOT AS MUCH AS I SHOULD.

09:18.759 --> 09:21.629
GOOD.
I THINK THAT'S GOOD.

09:21.695 --> 09:24.031
FOLKS READ TOO MUCH OF IT.
THEY JUST GET CONFUSED.

09:24.097 --> 09:27.935
THAT'S WHY I LIKE TO HAND OUT
JUST ONE CHAPTER AT A TIME.

09:28.001 --> 09:33.106
THAT WAY, FOLKS CAN DEAL WITH
THEIR CONFUSION AS IT COMES.

09:34.407 --> 09:38.278
COME ON. COME ON.
YOU'RE COMIN' WITH ME.
COME ON.

09:38.345 --> 09:42.415
I'M NOT GONNA LET YOU
GET AWAY EMPTY-HANDED.

09:42.482 --> 09:47.454
NOW, ON BEHALF OF THE MERCHANTS
AND BUSINESSMEN'S ASSOCIATION...

09:47.520 --> 09:49.322
OF THE CITY
OF SEQUOYAH, OKLAHOMA,

09:49.389 --> 09:53.493
I DO PRESENT YOU WITH THIS
BASKET OF GIFTS AND MERCHANDISE.

09:53.560 --> 09:57.297
THANK YOU.
LOOKY HERE, RUTH ANN,
YOU GOT, UM, DISCOUNT COUPONS...

09:57.364 --> 10:01.301
AND MATCHES, A MAP OF THE CITY,
EMERY BOARDS-- OH, OH, YEAH.

10:01.368 --> 10:05.205
NOW, YOU SEE THIS
LITTLE APPOINTMENT BOOK?
I RAN OUT OF THESE LAST WEEK,

10:05.272 --> 10:08.208
SO I HAD TO PUT TWO OR THREE
OF MY OWN APPOINTMENTS
IN THIS ONE,

10:08.275 --> 10:11.244
BUT IF YOU'RE NOT AN ALCOHOLIC,
YOU'LL KNOW THOSE MEETIN'S
AREN'T FOR YOU.

10:11.311 --> 10:15.248
NO, MA'AM, I'M NOT.
GOOD.
I THINK THAT'S GOOD.

10:15.315 --> 10:18.952
OH, YEAH, ONE MORE THING.

10:20.553 --> 10:25.525
WHAT IS THAT?
THIS IS A BUCKEYE TREE.
BRINGS YOU GOOD LUCK.

10:25.592 --> 10:28.929
HERE, TAKE IT.
THERE.

10:28.996 --> 10:32.499
WELL, GOOD-BYE, RUTH ANN.

10:32.565 --> 10:37.204
YOU KNOW IT WAS REAL NICE
TO SEE YOU AGAIN. HMM.
AND WELCOME HOME!

10:42.075 --> 10:45.713
I'M IN THE PHONE BOOK.
YOU COME AND SEE ME
ANYTIME YOU WANT.

10:45.779 --> 10:47.915
AND BRING THAT BABY.

10:50.951 --> 10:52.953
[ Engine Starts,
Backfires ]

11:32.159 --> 11:34.862
EXCUSE ME.

11:34.928 --> 11:38.165
WOULD YOU LIKE
A PICTURE OF YOUR BABY?
HMM?

11:38.231 --> 11:42.035
I'M NOT--
I MEAN, I'M STILL--
OH, WELL, I MEAN, AFTER.

11:42.102 --> 11:45.739
OH!
[ Chuckling ]
OF COURSE.

11:45.806 --> 11:48.675
WOW! WHAT KIND
OF CAMERA IS THAT?

11:48.742 --> 11:50.610
THIS IS A ROLLEI.

11:50.677 --> 11:53.947
THERE ARE NOT MANY MADE
LIKE THIS HERE.
IT'S A BEAUTY.

11:54.014 --> 11:56.583
MY NAME IS MOSES--
MOSES WHITECOTTON.

11:56.649 --> 11:58.852
NOVALEE NATION.

11:58.919 --> 12:01.154
NOVALEE NATION--
THAT'S A GOOD STRONG NAME.

12:01.221 --> 12:04.024
YOU KNOW,
A NAME'S IMPORTANT.

12:04.091 --> 12:06.894
HAVE YOU PICKED OUT A NAME
FOR YOUR BABY YET?

12:06.960 --> 12:10.697
WELL, I WAS THINKIN' ABOUT
"WENDI" WITH AN "I."

12:10.764 --> 12:13.466
OH, DON'T YOU DARE.

12:13.533 --> 12:17.570
GIVE THAT BABY A NAME
THAT MEANS SOMETHIN',
A GOOD, STURDY NAME.

12:17.637 --> 12:21.341
HERE.

12:21.408 --> 12:25.813
I'M HERE THE FIRST FRIDAY
OF EVERY MONTH, 12:00 TO 6:00.
TAKE CARE.

12:28.248 --> 12:31.985
AND REMEMBER:
GIVE THAT BABY A NAME
THAT MEANS SOMETHIN', YOU HEAR?

12:33.253 --> 12:35.455
I WILL, I PROMISE.

12:38.058 --> 12:39.960
[ Woman Over P.A. ]
ATTENTION, WAL-MART SHOPPERS.

12:40.027 --> 12:43.330
IT IS 9:00,
AND WAL-MART IS CLOSING.

12:43.396 --> 12:47.267
PLEASE BRING
YOUR FINAL SELECTIONS
TO THE CHECKOUT COUNTERS.

12:47.334 --> 12:51.171
WAL-MART WILL OPEN AGAIN
AT 9:00 TOMORROW MORNING,

12:51.238 --> 12:54.975
AND, AS ALWAYS,
THANK YOU FOR SHOPPING WAL-MART.

12:58.778 --> 13:00.647
[ Gasps Softly ]

13:00.713 --> 13:03.917
OH. OH.

13:03.984 --> 13:06.386
[ Coughing ]

13:07.654 --> 13:09.489
[ Toilet Flushes ]

13:46.626 --> 13:49.229
[ Radio ]
* YOU SAID YOU WAS
THE KING OF LOVE *

13:49.296 --> 13:51.298
** [ Continues, Indistinct ]

14:14.354 --> 14:16.856
- HI.
- HEY.

14:16.924 --> 14:19.492
YOU, UH--
YOU NEED A HAND?

14:20.627 --> 14:22.462
I NEED A LIFT.

14:24.831 --> 14:26.967
SO, WHERE YOU GOIN'?

14:27.034 --> 14:30.938
ANYWHERE BUT HERE.
WHERE YOU GOIN'?

14:31.004 --> 14:34.074
VEGAS.
COOL.

14:36.476 --> 14:39.212
WHOA-WHOA-WHOA.
HEY, HEY. NO. NO.

14:49.522 --> 14:51.391
THANKS.

16:16.009 --> 16:20.847
* WE COULD WAIT ON THAT PLAN
MAKE ALL NEW STRATEGY *

16:20.913 --> 16:25.452
* AND WHEN IT HITS THE FAN
MAKE IT WHAT
WE WANT IT TO BE *

16:25.518 --> 16:31.224
* AND WANNA GET HIGHER THEN
HIGHER THAN YOU'VE EVER BEEN *

16:31.291 --> 16:34.427
* WHAT ABOUT YOU
WHAT ABOUT YOU *

16:34.494 --> 16:39.232
* SHAKE IT UP, SHAKE IT DOWN
YOU CAN FEEL IT ALL AROUND **

16:40.733 --> 16:43.403
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

16:54.614 --> 16:58.585
[ Radio ]
* I KNOW
THAT YOUR MEMORY LIVES *

16:58.651 --> 17:01.288
[ Girl ] YOU KNOW,
YOU'RE ALMOST OUT OF GAS.
YEAH.

17:01.354 --> 17:06.159
SOME SON OF A BITCH STOLE
MY WALLET LAST NIGHT RIGHT
OUT OF MY DAMN HOTEL ROOM.

17:09.729 --> 17:12.332
MAYBE THIS'LL HELP.

17:12.398 --> 17:14.300
HEY!

17:17.604 --> 17:22.075
WELL, I TELL YOU WHAT.
YOU WANT IT?

17:22.142 --> 17:25.478
GLIDE ON OVER HERE
AND GET IT.

17:25.545 --> 17:28.147
MAYBE I WILL.

17:28.214 --> 17:30.817
MAYBE YOU'LL GET YOURSELF
A NICE BIG SURPRISE.

17:36.123 --> 17:38.325
[ Siren Blaring ]

17:40.360 --> 17:42.995
SHIT.

17:43.062 --> 17:48.301
$218 IN YOUR POCKET
AND 14 CARTONS OF
WINSTON LIGHT 100s...

17:48.368 --> 17:51.738
IN A PLASTIC SACK
IN THE TRUNK OF YOUR CAR.

17:51.804 --> 17:56.143
BY THE STRANGEST DAMN
COINCIDENCE, THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT SOMEONE STOLE...

17:56.209 --> 17:59.312
FROM THE 7-11 STORE
ABOUT TWO HOURS AGO.

17:59.379 --> 18:03.183
NOT TO MENTION--
JOLENE, HOW OLD ARE YOU
THESE DAYS?

18:03.250 --> 18:06.686
FOURTEEN.
OH? FOURTEEN.

18:08.221 --> 18:10.290
[ Grunting ]

18:13.526 --> 18:19.366
[ Alarm Clock Rings,
Clicks Off ]

18:39.952 --> 18:43.223
[ Voices ]

18:45.825 --> 18:47.727
[ Chattering ]

18:50.029 --> 18:53.300
I CLEANED THE BATHROOM
THE OTHER DAY.
AND YOU DID SUCH A GOOD JOB...

18:53.366 --> 18:56.336
YOU GET TO DO IT AGAIN!
[ All Laugh ]

19:30.837 --> 19:33.506
[ Prisoner ]
HEY, SWEET THING.

19:37.410 --> 19:41.180
- ** [ Radio Starts ]
- [ Alarm Clock Rings ]

19:58.565 --> 20:00.633
* COMES DOWN
TO JUST ONE MOMENT *

20:00.700 --> 20:03.736
* NO WAY
YOU CAN CONTROL IT *

20:03.803 --> 20:08.107
* SOMEHOW YOUR HEART WILL KNOW
THE PLACE AND TIME *

20:08.174 --> 20:12.379
* IT WON'T CHANGE YOUR WORLD
BUT IT JUST MIGHT CHANGE
YOUR LIFE **

20:26.726 --> 20:28.595
[ Cooing ]

21:15.675 --> 21:18.711
[ Man ]
WHAT DO YOU WANT?
UH,

21:18.778 --> 21:22.048
I'M LOOKIN' FOR--
FOR A BOOK.

21:22.114 --> 21:24.116
WHAT KIND OF BOOK?

21:24.183 --> 21:27.354
ABOUT-- ABOUT TREES.

21:28.254 --> 21:30.590
TREES?

21:30.657 --> 21:32.725
YEAH.

21:34.260 --> 21:37.430
YOU KNOW.

21:37.497 --> 21:41.468
FORESTRY? ENVIRONMENT?
AGRICULTURE? BOTANY? WHAT DO
YOU WANT TO KNOW ABOUT TREES?

21:41.534 --> 21:45.338
WELL, A FEW WEEKS AGO
SOMEBODY GAVE ME A BUCKEYE TREE.

21:45.405 --> 21:49.275
BUCKEYE-- HORSE CHESTNUT--

21:49.342 --> 21:53.946
BELONGS TO THE GENUS AESCULUS,
OF THE FAMILY HIPPOCASTANACCAE.

21:54.013 --> 21:58.217
I-I THINK IT'S DYIN'-- MY TREE.
I COULD SHOW IT TO THE PEOPLE
WHO GAVE IT TO ME,

21:58.284 --> 22:01.153
BUT I'M EMBARRASSED TO LET THEM
SEE HOW SICK I LET IT GET.

22:01.220 --> 22:04.591
THERE. LOOK UP "BUCKEYE"
IN THE INDEX.
THE WHAT?

22:04.657 --> 22:07.694
I'LL START SLOWER.
THESE ARE CALLED "BOOKS."

22:07.760 --> 22:10.563
ARE YOU STILL WITH ME?
HERE.
HEY.

22:12.999 --> 22:16.636
UH, THERE. SEE? READ.

22:16.703 --> 22:20.373
"LEAF ROT. ROOT DAMAGE.
NIT-- NITRO--

22:20.440 --> 22:24.210
"NIT-- NITROGEN D-- DEF--

22:24.276 --> 22:28.014
DEFIC--"
[ Sighs ]

22:28.080 --> 22:32.184
- "DEFIC--"
- DEFICIENCY!
KEEP READING.

22:32.251 --> 22:34.921
ALSO BUCKEYE--

22:34.987 --> 22:36.856
MM-HMM.

22:37.890 --> 22:40.460
[ Glass Breaks,
Woman Cries Out ]

22:42.328 --> 22:44.631
EXCUSE ME.

22:49.469 --> 22:51.538
[ Door Opens ]

22:53.906 --> 22:56.809
WELL, I DON'T KNOW
HOW I COULD HAVE MADE
SUCH A MISTAKE.

22:56.876 --> 22:59.746
YOU DON'T LOOK LIKE
RUTH ANN AT ALL, DO YOU?
[ Laughs ]

22:59.812 --> 23:02.649
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU
AGAIN, DARLIN'.
YOU COME RIGHT ON IN.

23:02.715 --> 23:07.353
I WANT YOU TO MEET
MY GENTLEMAN, MR. SPROCK.

23:07.420 --> 23:10.623
MR. SPROCK? MR. SPROCK.
HMM?

23:10.690 --> 23:15.662
- OH, HOW DO YOU DO?
- BUTTERMILK?

23:23.102 --> 23:27.440
DEAR LORD,
WE PRAY THAT YOU WILL
BLESS THIS FOOD...

23:27.507 --> 23:30.009
TO THE NOURISHMENT
OF OUR BODIES,

23:30.076 --> 23:34.614
AND WE PRAY, LORD,
FOR A SAFE DELIVERY
AND A HEALTHY CHILD...

23:34.681 --> 23:37.283
FOR OUR NEW FRIEND.

23:37.349 --> 23:41.921
AND WE ASK FORGIVENESS,
LORD, FOR THE FORNICATION
THAT MR. SPROCK AND ME...

23:41.988 --> 23:45.057
HAVE COMMITTED AGAIN
THIS AFTERNOON.

23:45.124 --> 23:47.426
AMEN.

23:47.494 --> 23:50.096
- AMEN.
- AMEN.

23:55.101 --> 23:58.304
I'LL COME BY EVERY DAY
TO TAKE CARE OF IT.
YOU WON'T HAVE TO DO A THING.

23:58.370 --> 24:01.407
OH, GOOD.
NOW, IF IT'S ANY KIND
OF BOTHER, I COULD--

24:01.474 --> 24:04.977
OH, NO, NO, DARLIN'.
I MEANT IT'S GOOD
THAT YOU'LL BE BY EVERY DAY.

24:05.044 --> 24:09.949
- WHY, WE'D SURE BE
GLAD TO SEE YOU.
- OH.

24:10.016 --> 24:12.218
ALTHOUGH, YOU KNOW,
I HAVE TO SAY,

24:12.284 --> 24:15.522
I DON'T KNOW WHAT KIND
OF PEOPLE YOU'RE STAYING WITH
THAT WON'T LET YOU PLANT A TREE.

24:15.588 --> 24:18.925
WELL, THEY'RE--
AND WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN
WHEN YOU HAVE YOUR BABY?

24:20.426 --> 24:23.830
I-- I'M NOT SURE.

24:23.896 --> 24:26.232
LET ME HELP YOU THERE,
MR. SPROCK.

24:28.067 --> 24:32.238
- HEY, ROSITA!
HOW YOU DOIN' TODAY?
- GOOD!

24:34.941 --> 24:37.076
[ Sighs ]

24:37.143 --> 24:39.411
YOU KNOW, THE BOOK
IN THE "LIBARY" SAID
THE HIGHEST SPOT IN THE YARD...

24:39.478 --> 24:44.050
IS THE BEST PLACE
TO PLANT THE TREE.
OH, YOU MUST HAVE MET FORNEY.

24:44.116 --> 24:46.018
WHO?
[ Wheezing ]

24:46.085 --> 24:48.187
[ Continues Wheezing ]

24:48.254 --> 24:52.592
- YOU ALL RIGHT, MR. SPROCK?
- OH, I'M FINE.
A LITTLE EMPHYSEMA.

24:52.659 --> 24:57.830
IT'S NOTHIN' SERIOUS.
YOU KNOW, HE MAKES THAT NOISE
WHENEVER HE EXERTS HIMSELF?

24:58.831 --> 25:01.267
WHO'S "THORNY"?
FORNEY.

25:01.333 --> 25:05.471
FORNEY HULL--
BRILLIANT MAN,
LIVES IN THE "LIBARY."

25:05.538 --> 25:08.641
BRILLIANT.
THERE'S NO TELLIN' WHAT HE MIGHT
HAVE DONE IN THIS WORLD...

25:08.708 --> 25:10.610
IF HE'D BEEN ALLOWED
TO FINISH HIS SCHOOLIN'.

25:10.677 --> 25:13.846
WHY DIDN'T HE?

25:13.913 --> 25:15.915
THE LORD GIVES US OBSTACLES.

25:18.350 --> 25:21.253
[ Train Whistle Blowing ]

25:47.146 --> 25:49.015
[ Gasps ]

25:50.750 --> 25:52.719
[ Thunder Rumbles ]

26:01.694 --> 26:04.430
[ Gasps, Moans ]

26:04.496 --> 26:06.633
[ Panting ]

26:14.506 --> 26:17.576
[ Gasps, Moans ]

26:29.689 --> 26:32.358
[ Thunder Rumbles ]

26:43.269 --> 26:45.337
[ Groaning ]

26:57.383 --> 27:00.219
[ Sobbing ]

27:05.424 --> 27:07.293
[ Cries Out ]

27:13.165 --> 27:17.970
[ Wailing ]

27:22.742 --> 27:25.712
[ Continues
Whimpering, Crying ]

27:42.661 --> 27:45.732
[ Grunting ]

27:47.299 --> 27:50.302
[ Screaming ]

27:58.244 --> 28:01.013
[ Screaming Echoes ]

28:14.994 --> 28:17.229
I HOPE YOU'RE NOT HUNGRY,
'CAUSE IT'S TUESDAY.

28:19.465 --> 28:22.568
FRIDAY IS
THE BEST BREAKFAST DAY--
THEY HAVE BACON.

28:22.634 --> 28:25.838
I'M LEXIE--
LEXIE COOP.
HI.

28:25.905 --> 28:28.808
HI.
WHERE'D ALL THESE FLOWERS
COME FROM?

28:28.875 --> 28:31.210
ALL OVER.
YOU'RE A BIG CELEBRITY.

28:31.277 --> 28:34.046
THEY'RE REPORTERS HERE.
LEAN UP.

28:36.615 --> 28:38.717
SEE?

28:41.520 --> 28:44.791
- TV! THEY'VE
BEEN HERE ALL NIGHT.
- WHAT FOR?

28:44.857 --> 28:47.760
FOR YOU!
THEY WANNA TALK TO YOU.

28:47.827 --> 28:49.728
- ME?
- OF COURSE.

28:49.796 --> 28:52.331
EVERYBODY WANTS
TO TALK TO THE MOTHER
OF THE WAL-MART BABY.

28:52.398 --> 28:56.102
- AM I IN TROUBLE?
ARE THEY GONNA ARREST ME?
- WHAT FOR?

28:56.168 --> 29:00.239
- FOR LIVIN' IN THE WAL-MART.
- ARREST YOU?

29:00.306 --> 29:03.943
IS THE HOSPITAL GONNA
KEEP MY BABY?
WHERE IS SHE?

29:04.010 --> 29:07.046
- WHY WOULD THE HOSPITAL
KEEP YOUR BABY?
- BECAUSE I CAN'T PAY.

29:07.113 --> 29:11.750
IT'S LIKE-- IT'S LIKE
A RESTAURANT-- WHEN YOU CAN'T
PAY, THEY MAKE YOU WASH DISHES.

29:11.818 --> 29:15.087
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
THEY'RE GONNA MAKE ME DO.

29:15.154 --> 29:18.991
NO. NO.
I'M BROKE. I GOT NOTHIN'.

29:19.058 --> 29:22.895
I HAVE NO FAMILY, NO JOB,
AND I GOT A BABY.

29:23.996 --> 29:27.033
I KNOW WHAT YOU NEED.

29:30.636 --> 29:35.141
[ Gurgling ]
YES, YOU'RE OKAY.
LOOK WHO WE'RE GOING TO SEE.

29:35.207 --> 29:38.177
[ Gasps ]
SAY "IT'S ABOUT TIME."

29:47.653 --> 29:50.422
- DOES THAT HELP?
- [ Gurgling ]

29:50.489 --> 29:52.358
OH, OH, YEAH.

29:53.559 --> 29:57.163
HOW CAN YOU LOVE SOMEONE
SO MUCH YOU JUST MET?

29:59.932 --> 30:04.170
FORNEY'S OKAY TOO.
DOCTOR STITCHED HIM UP
AND SENT HIM ON HOME.

30:04.236 --> 30:06.973
FORNEY?
THE "LIBARY" GUY?
MM-HMM.

30:07.039 --> 30:09.808
YEAH.
WHY?
WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM?

30:09.876 --> 30:13.179
HE JUMPED THROUGH
A PLATE-GLASS WINDOW
TO DELIVER YOUR BABY.

30:13.245 --> 30:15.481
DON'T YOU REMEMBER?
THAT WAS HIM ?

30:17.616 --> 30:20.152
[ Fussing ]
OH.

30:20.219 --> 30:24.123
SO, WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA NAME HER?

30:25.091 --> 30:27.693
OH, THAT'S RIGHT.

30:27.759 --> 30:31.697
[ Lexie ] "AMERICUS"?
HOW THE HELL'D YOU COME UP
WITH A NAME LIKE AMERICUS?

30:31.763 --> 30:35.935
[ Novalee ] I WANTED HER
TO HAVE A STRONG NAME,
A NAME THAT STOOD FOR SOMETHIN'.

30:36.002 --> 30:39.705
OOH. AW.
[ Baby Crying ]

30:39.771 --> 30:42.975
WELL, I GUESS I SHOULD TALK.
I CALL MY KIDS AFTER
SNACK FOODS:

30:43.042 --> 30:45.311
BROWNIE, PRALINE,
CHERRY AND BABY RUTH.

30:45.377 --> 30:48.047
YOU GOT FOUR?
YOU DON'T LOOK OLD ENOUGH.
YEP.

30:48.114 --> 30:51.250
WELL, I STARTED WHEN I WAS 15,
AND I JUST COULDN'T STOP.

30:51.317 --> 30:55.387
I WANTED TO FIND THE FIRST ONE
A DADDY, BUT ALL I GOT
OUT OF THAT WAS ANOTHER BABY.

30:55.454 --> 30:58.757
SO, I WANTED TO FIND 'EM BOTH
A DADDY, AND SO ON, AND SO ON.

30:58.824 --> 31:01.827
I THINK I'M GOIN' ABOUT THIS
THE WRONG WAY.
[ Chuckles ]

31:01.894 --> 31:05.031
HEY! THERE SHE IS!
THAT'S THE WAL-MART MOMMY!

31:05.097 --> 31:08.467
NOW, HOW LONG WERE YOU
LIVING IN THE WAL-MART?

31:11.303 --> 31:14.006
UH, UH,

31:14.073 --> 31:17.609
SIX WEEKS.
AND WHAT WAS IT LIKE?

31:21.580 --> 31:23.482
YOU KNOW.

31:24.716 --> 31:26.785
[ Giggles ]

31:26.852 --> 31:29.155
HAVE YOU SPOKEN
TO THE FATHER?

31:31.623 --> 31:36.295
NOVALEE, IF I WAS YOU,
I'D RULE OUT A CAREER
IN BROADCASTIN'.

31:36.362 --> 31:40.832
WHY WOULD ANYONE
WRITE ANYTHING SO HURTFUL?
WHAT'S IT SAY?

31:40.899 --> 31:46.038
"A BABY BORN OUT OF HOLY WEDLOCK
IS AN ABOMINATION
IN THE EYES OF GOD."

31:46.105 --> 31:49.041
[ Sighs ]
MY BABY IS NOT
AN ABOMINATION.

31:49.108 --> 31:52.511
SCREW 'EM.
MIDNIGHT, MISSISSIPPI.

31:59.318 --> 32:03.455
OH, MY.
THIS ONE'S SAD.

32:03.522 --> 32:08.094
"I GAVE BIRTH TO A BABY
IN A V.W. VAN WHERE I LIVED
FOR NEARLY A YEAR."

32:08.160 --> 32:11.930
[ Sighs ]
"MY BABY DIDN'T MAKE IT.
I HOPE YOURS DOES.

32:11.998 --> 32:15.101
"I DON'T HAVE MUCH ELSE
TO OFFER YOU, BUT I KNOW
THAT SOME MONEY MIGHT HELP,

32:15.167 --> 32:17.936
SO I ENCLOSE $10."

32:19.105 --> 32:21.540
CAN YOU BELIEVE THAT?

32:27.113 --> 32:29.548
"DUDA," TEXAS.
[ Chuckles ]

32:30.949 --> 32:33.852
"I WISH I COULD SEND YOU SOME
MONEY, BUT I DON'T HAVE ANY.

32:33.919 --> 32:36.522
WHAT I CAN OFFER YOU IS
A GOOD HOME."

32:36.588 --> 32:38.424
SEND HER THE $10.

32:39.925 --> 32:42.461
LEXIE, ONE OF YOUR KIDS IS
ON THE PHONE.

32:42.528 --> 32:44.663
WHICH ONE?

32:44.730 --> 32:48.267
I DON'T KNOW.
PEZ, TWINKIE--
ONE OF 'EM.

32:48.334 --> 32:52.604
- [ Scoffs ]
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.
- [ Giggles ]

32:57.143 --> 32:59.211
[ Woman ]
IS NOVALEE IN THERE?
[ Lexie ] YES, MA'AM.

33:04.616 --> 33:06.518
WELL,

33:06.585 --> 33:10.489
I HOPE YOU DON'T THINK
THIS KID'S GONNA
CALL ME "GRANDMA."

33:10.556 --> 33:12.724
I'M SORRY, MA'AM, BUT
VISITING HOURS ARE NOT UNTIL--
[ Gasps ]

33:12.791 --> 33:15.061
ARE WHEN?
RIGHT NOW.

33:15.127 --> 33:17.329
YES. THANK YOU.

33:19.398 --> 33:23.069
- MAMA?
- I THOUGHT
YOU'D BE SURPRISED.

33:25.471 --> 33:29.375
- HOW'D YOU KNOW I WAS HERE?
- THERE YA ARE.

33:31.277 --> 33:35.047
I SAW YOUR FABULOUS INTERVIEW
ON THE TELEVISION,

33:35.114 --> 33:38.384
AND I HOPPED RIGHT IN THE CAR,
AND HERE I AM.

33:40.286 --> 33:44.623
OH, I MUST HAVE BEEN
IN THAT DAMN CAR, LIKE,
TEN HOURS, I'M TELLIN' YOU.

33:44.690 --> 33:47.226
FROM WHERE?

33:48.894 --> 33:50.762
NEW ORLEANS.

33:52.331 --> 33:55.934
I BEEN LIVIN' THERE
ABOUT, UM--

33:56.001 --> 33:57.903
HUH.

33:57.969 --> 34:00.872
I GUESS I BEEN LIVIN' THERE
ABOUT TWO, THREE YEARS NOW.

34:00.939 --> 34:03.175
- WITH FRED?
- WHO?

34:03.242 --> 34:05.577
FRED, THE UMPIRE.

34:05.644 --> 34:08.045
[ Scoffs ]

34:09.047 --> 34:12.083
THAT SHITHEAD?
OH, MY GOD!

34:12.150 --> 34:14.585
[ Laughing ]
JESUS!

34:14.652 --> 34:16.822
WHAT IN GOD'S NAME
MADE YOU THINK OF HIM?

34:19.324 --> 34:21.927
BECAUSE HE WAS
THE REASON YOU LEFT.

34:21.993 --> 34:25.563
- LEFT WHAT?
- ME.

34:26.864 --> 34:30.502
OH, GEEZ. NOW,

34:30.569 --> 34:32.438
SWEETIE, LOOK.

34:32.504 --> 34:35.474
[ Scoffs ]
THAT IS ALL
WATER UNDER THE BRIDGE.

34:35.541 --> 34:38.310
I DIDN'T DRIVE HERE
FOR TEN HOURS TO REMINISCE
WITH YOU, ALL RIGHT?

34:38.377 --> 34:41.480
- WELL, THEN WHY DID YOU COME?
- WELL, I THOUGHT
YOU COULD USE SOME HELP.

34:41.547 --> 34:43.882
YOU DIDN'T LOOK
TOO GOOD UP THERE.
YOU--

34:43.949 --> 34:47.886
LIVIN' IN THE WAL-MART IS
NOT MY IDEA OF A BIG SUCCESS.

34:47.953 --> 34:51.157
- HOW ARE YOU GONNA HELP?
- I DON'T KNOW.

34:53.992 --> 34:56.395
- YOU GOT A MAN?
- NO.

34:56.462 --> 34:59.765
IT'S NOT ONE OF THOSE
ARTIFICIAL "SPERMINATION"
THINGS IS IT?

34:59.831 --> 35:01.600
NO.

35:01.667 --> 35:04.836
THEN WHERE IS THE PRICK
WHO PUT YOU IN THIS MESS?

35:04.903 --> 35:07.139
CALIFORNIA.

35:07.206 --> 35:10.442
[ Laughs ]
WELL, THAT FIGURES.

35:10.509 --> 35:13.212
ALL THE PRICKS--
THEY MOVE TO CALIFORNIA.

35:13.279 --> 35:15.514
THEY OUGHT TO CALL IT
"PRICK-IFORNIA."

35:19.785 --> 35:21.753
GOT A PLACE TO LIVE?

35:23.255 --> 35:27.726
SWEETIE, LOOK.
YOU ARE GOING TO NEED A PLACE
TO TAKE THIS BABY.

35:27.793 --> 35:31.797
MAYBE YOU SHOULD THINK
ABOUT MOVIN' INTO SEARS.
I HEAR KMART IS REALLY NICE.

35:31.863 --> 35:34.600
DID YOU COME ALL THIS WAY
JUST TO MAKE FUN OF ME?

35:34.666 --> 35:37.569
GOD, NO.

35:37.636 --> 35:40.272
JESUS.

35:40.339 --> 35:44.176
[ Stamping Out Ash ]
I DIDN'T. I WANTED...

35:44.243 --> 35:47.513
[ Laughing Nervously ]
TO HELP MY CHILD
WITH HER CHILD, IS ALL.

35:51.283 --> 35:54.686
- YOU WANT ME TO GO?
- NO.

35:56.488 --> 35:58.924
ALL RIGHT THEN.
[ Chuckles ]

35:58.990 --> 36:01.360
- WHEN ARE THEY
LETTIN' YOU OUT?
- TOMORROW.

36:02.661 --> 36:04.530
HMM.

36:04.596 --> 36:07.766
WELL, I'M NOT
IN ANY HURRY TO MOVE ON.

36:07.833 --> 36:11.703
MAYBE I COULD FIND A PLACE--
YOU AND ME AND THE BABY.

36:13.171 --> 36:15.807
YOU MEAN LIKE--
LIKE A HOME?

36:17.743 --> 36:19.678
UH--

36:19.745 --> 36:22.614
HOME, APARTMENT, WHATEVER--
TILL YOU GET ON YOUR FEET.

36:22.681 --> 36:25.016
I GOT ME A LITTLE MONEY.
[ Chuckles ]

36:25.083 --> 36:29.555
OH, I GOT MONEY.
THE PRESIDENT OF WAL-MART
SENT ME $500.

36:31.857 --> 36:33.759
WHY?

36:35.994 --> 36:39.331
- HE'S NOT THE FATHER
OF THE CHILD, IS HE?
- NO.

36:39.398 --> 36:43.369
- AW, SHIT.
- NO, HE JUST WANTED
TO BE NICE.

36:43.435 --> 36:47.005
THEY OFFERED ME ANY JOB
IN ANY WAL-MART IN THE COUNTRY.

36:47.072 --> 36:48.874
WOW.
[ Chuckles ]

36:50.776 --> 36:52.678
SO.

36:56.315 --> 36:59.184
I'M THINKIN',

36:59.251 --> 37:02.888
WHAT WITH YOUR MONEY
AND MY MONEY TOGETHER,

37:02.954 --> 37:05.524
WE MIGHT BE ABLE TO FIND US
A REAL DECENT PLACE,

37:05.591 --> 37:09.861
SO I DON'T WANT YOU
TO WORRY ABOUT ANYTHING ANYMORE,

37:09.928 --> 37:12.230
'CAUSE MAMA LIL IS HERE NOW.

37:12.298 --> 37:16.835
WHY DON'T YOU COME BY
AND PICK US UP TOMORROW--
ME AND AMERICUS-- 9:00 A.M.?

37:18.637 --> 37:20.672
ON THE DOT.
[ Chuckles ]

37:27.012 --> 37:32.250
SO, I GOT ME A LOT OF STUFF
TO DO. WE GOTTA GET
DIAPERS AND BLANKETS...

37:32.318 --> 37:34.320
AND A CRADLE.

37:34.386 --> 37:36.888
- MAMA?
- YEAH?

37:36.955 --> 37:38.757
THANK YOU FOR COMIN'.

37:40.326 --> 37:42.428
YOU BET.

37:45.797 --> 37:47.633
[ Baby Fussing ]

37:53.204 --> 37:55.140
IT'S OKAY, BABY.
IT'S OKAY.

37:55.206 --> 37:57.275
YOU'RE OKAY.

38:05.884 --> 38:08.754
MAYBE YOU SHOULD TRY TO CALL
WHOEVER'S PICKIN' YOU UP.

38:08.820 --> 38:11.289
I DON'T KNOW
WHERE SHE'S STAYIN'.

38:11.357 --> 38:13.892
I COULD CALL A CAB FOR YOU.
WHERE YOU GOIN'?

38:19.365 --> 38:21.400
[ Baby Crying ]

38:29.941 --> 38:32.811
FIVE HUNDRED DOLLARS--
I SHOULD HAVE KNOWN.

38:44.289 --> 38:46.458
[ Horn Honking ]

38:56.067 --> 38:58.704
HEY.

39:05.877 --> 39:08.113
[ Sighs ]

39:08.179 --> 39:10.382
WELL, LOOK AT ALL THIS.

39:10.449 --> 39:13.652
[ Chuckles ]
AND LOOK AT YOU.

39:13.719 --> 39:16.955
OH, YES, YOU'RE JUST AS CUTE
TODAY AS YOU WERE YESTERDAY,

39:18.690 --> 39:21.059
MAYBE CUTER.
YEAH.

39:23.328 --> 39:27.866
WELL, YOU KNOW THAT TREE--

39:27.933 --> 39:31.169
YOUR TREE THAT YOU PLANTED
IN MY YARD?

39:31.236 --> 39:34.406
I'VE BEEN TRYIN'
TO TAKE CARE OF IT, AND I JUST
DON'T HAVE THE FEEL FOR IT.

39:34.473 --> 39:37.108
I DON'T HAVE THE TIME
EITHER.

39:37.175 --> 39:41.980
SO, I THOUGHT MAYBE
IF YOU AND THE BABY CAME
TO STAY WITH ME FOR A WHILE...

39:42.047 --> 39:44.450
THAT YOU COULD
TAKE CARE OF IT FOR ME.

39:46.084 --> 39:48.153
SURE HELP ME OUT A LOT.

39:49.888 --> 39:51.790
OKAY.

40:02.267 --> 40:04.202
[ Woman ]
FORNEY!
WHAT?

40:04.269 --> 40:07.673
WHERE ARE YOU?
I'M JUST PUTTING
THE DISHES IN THE SINK.

40:07.739 --> 40:11.076
FORNEY?
I'LL BE--
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

40:11.142 --> 40:14.980
- FORNEY. FORNEY!
- [ Knocking ]
- WE'RE CLOSED!

40:16.982 --> 40:19.618
LOOK, WE'RE--

40:19.685 --> 40:21.987
HI.

40:22.053 --> 40:23.922
CAN I COME IN?

40:23.989 --> 40:26.357
UH, YEAH.

40:26.424 --> 40:28.994
I NEED A TOWEL!
THEY'RE IN THE BATHROOM!

40:29.060 --> 40:32.330
IS THIS A BAD TIME?
UH, YEAH. NO.
[ Chuckles Nervously ]

40:32.397 --> 40:34.900
I JUST-- I JUST WANTED
TO THANK YOU FOR--

40:34.966 --> 40:39.004
I CAN'T REACH THEM!
GIVE ME TWO MINUTES!

40:39.070 --> 40:41.740
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

40:41.807 --> 40:46.011
SORRY, I--
THAT'S OKAY, I--

40:46.077 --> 40:51.116
I JUST WANTED TO THANK YOU
FOR-- WELL, I GUESS YOU
SAVED OUR LIVES--

40:51.182 --> 40:53.619
ME AND AMERICUS.
"AMERICUS"?

40:56.387 --> 40:58.624
YOU WANNA HOLD HER?

40:58.690 --> 41:01.827
OH--
IT'S OKAY.

41:04.295 --> 41:06.765
OH, OH, OH.
[ Gasps ]

41:08.900 --> 41:11.970
MOSES WHITECOTTON GAVE ME
THIS AS A BABY GIFT.

41:12.037 --> 41:14.806
UH-HUH.
OH.

41:16.942 --> 41:19.210
HAT.

41:23.515 --> 41:28.486
ALL RIGHT.
ONE, TWO, THREE, SMILE.

41:30.421 --> 41:33.625
FORNEY!
I--

41:36.294 --> 41:39.264
ALL RIGHT. SO,

41:40.966 --> 41:43.201
I'LL SEE YOU SOON.
UH-HUH.

41:44.269 --> 41:46.137
OH, UH--

41:48.540 --> 41:50.676
GOOD-BYE.
BYE.

41:50.742 --> 41:53.178
FORNEY!
[ Sighs ]

42:01.252 --> 42:04.723
* YOU MAY FIND *
[ Inmate ]
SHUT UP!

42:04.790 --> 42:08.159
* LOOK INSIDE
AND FIND THE PART *

42:08.226 --> 42:10.228
[ Sighs ]

42:10.295 --> 42:16.034
* LOOK INSIDE AND FIND THE PART
THAT'S LEADIN' YOU **
SHUT THE HELL UP!

42:20.271 --> 42:22.874
JACK. HEY, JACK--

42:22.941 --> 42:25.376
[ Grunting ]
[ Inmates Yelling ]

42:25.443 --> 42:29.648
** [ Radio, Indistinct ]

42:29.715 --> 42:33.118
WHAT DO YOU THINK?
IT TOOK ME A WHOLE MONTH
TO GET BACK TO MY OLD SIZE.

42:33.184 --> 42:35.621
[ Gurgling ]

42:35.687 --> 42:38.757
OH, WELL, A LITTLE WEIGHT
ON A WOMAN'S NO HARM.

42:38.824 --> 42:40.826
HUH? WHAT DO YOU
THINK OF THAT?

42:40.892 --> 42:42.794
[ Chuckles ]
BREAKFAST?

42:42.861 --> 42:47.599
NO. BEFORE WORK I'M GONNA
TAKE YOUR TRUCK IN
AND GET THOSE BRAKES CHECKED.

42:47.666 --> 42:49.735
I'M PAYIN'. DON'T ARGUE.

42:49.801 --> 42:53.304
SISTER, THERE'S PEOPLE
AT THE DOOR.
OH, HERE. COME ON.

42:54.539 --> 42:56.474
COME ON.
THERE YA GO.
HELLO.

42:56.541 --> 42:59.510
THERE YA GO.
WHO'S A GOOD GIRL?
YES.

42:59.577 --> 43:01.647
I GOT HER.

43:03.615 --> 43:05.483
YES?
MA'AM,

43:05.550 --> 43:09.755
WE HAVE COME HERE TODAY
TO BRING THE WORD OF GOD
TO THE WAL-MART BABY...

43:09.821 --> 43:13.158
AND TO HER YOUNG,
UNMARRIED MAMA.

43:13.224 --> 43:17.763
WE DROVE ALL THE WAY UP
FROM MIDNIGHT, MISSISSIPPI.

43:17.829 --> 43:21.933
WELL, YOU FOLKS COULD HAVE
SAVED YOURSELF A TRIP,

43:22.000 --> 43:26.204
'CAUSE THE WORD OF GOD'S BEEN
IN THIS HOUSE A LONG TIME.

43:29.474 --> 43:32.911
[ Sighs ]
I THOUGHT THAT WAS
ALL OVER AND DONE WITH--

43:32.978 --> 43:36.247
PEOPLE WANTIN' TO SEE
THE WAL-MART BABY.

43:36.314 --> 43:38.684
BYE, SWEETIE.
MAMA WILL BE BACK.
[ Gurgles ]

43:38.750 --> 43:41.920
BYE, MR. SPROCK.
I MADE LINKS!

43:41.987 --> 43:43.855
THANK YOU.

43:45.056 --> 43:47.425
[ Sighs ]
DEAR LORD, WE PRAY...

43:47.492 --> 43:50.628
THAT YOU WILL BLESS THIS FOOD
FOR THE NOURISHMENT
OF OUR BODIES,

43:50.696 --> 43:55.667
AND WE ASK FORGIVENESS,
LORD, FOR THE FORNICATION
THAT MR. SPROCK AND ME...

43:55.734 --> 43:59.204
COMMITTED THIS MORNING
ON THIS VERY TABLE.

43:59.270 --> 44:01.139
AMEN.
AMEN.

44:07.112 --> 44:12.550
[ Radio ]
* ONLY YOU *

44:12.617 --> 44:14.886
* CAN MAKE THIS WORLD *

44:14.953 --> 44:17.522
[ Man ]
HEY, WHOA, WHOA!
YOU CAN'T PARK THERE!

44:17.588 --> 44:22.193
WE AIN'T OPEN YET.
I KNOW THAT,
BUT I GOTTA GET TO WORK.

44:22.260 --> 44:26.031
WELL, I'M WORKIN' TOO, AND
I GOTTA KEEP THE SIDEWALK CLEAR.
I'LL LEAVE YOU THE KEYS, THEN--

44:26.097 --> 44:30.035
* CAN MAKE THE DARKNESS BRIGHT *

44:31.436 --> 44:33.671
* ONLY YOU *

44:33.739 --> 44:37.008
* AND YOU ALONE *

44:38.609 --> 44:42.447
* CAN THRILL ME LIKE YOU DO **

44:42.513 --> 44:45.717
I THINK I MIGHT BE PREGNANT.

44:45.784 --> 44:48.319
YOU KNOW THAT GUY
I TOLD YOU ABOUT--
THE ONE I MET LAST MONTH?

44:48.386 --> 44:51.823
YEAH, THE GOOD-LOOKIN'
MECHANIC. HONEY--
YEAH.

44:51.890 --> 44:54.659
I DON'T KNOW WHAT'S WRONG
WITH ME. I DIDN'T EVEN WANT
TO BE WITH HIM.

44:54.726 --> 44:57.662
WELL, DIDN'T HE
USE ANYTHING?
JUST ME.

44:57.729 --> 45:00.766
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I'M GONNA DO.

45:00.832 --> 45:04.736
WELL, THIS OLD GYPSY WOMAN
ONCE TOLD ME THAT IF YOU
JUMP BACKWARDS NINE TIMES...

45:04.803 --> 45:06.872
BEFORE THE SUN COME UP,
YOU WON'T BE PREGNANT.

45:06.938 --> 45:12.110
SO I JUMPED SO FAR I HAD TO
TAKE A BUS TO GET BACK HOME,
AND THEN I HAD TWINS.

45:12.177 --> 45:14.946
[ Chuckles ]
WHICH IS WHY THE GUY I'M
SEEIN' NOW IS PRETTY PERFECT.

45:15.013 --> 45:17.849
WHY'S THAT?
WELL,

45:17.916 --> 45:20.218
HE'S STERILE
AS A COTTON BALL.

45:22.387 --> 45:25.791
SO IT'S PERMANENT?
OH, YEAH. HE HAD MUMPS
WHEN HE WAS 15...

45:25.857 --> 45:28.726
AND THEY WENT DOWN ON HIM.
DOWN WHERE?

45:28.794 --> 45:30.796
TO HIS MANLY AREAS.

45:30.862 --> 45:34.232
SO THEY'RE--
OH, GOD, NOVALEE, NO.

45:34.299 --> 45:36.734
HE'S JUST SHOOTIN' BLANKS,
IS ALL.

45:36.802 --> 45:40.038
WELL, LET'S FACE IT:
GIRLS LIKE US DON'T GET
THE PICK OF THE LITTER.

45:40.105 --> 45:43.741
I DON'T THINK YOU'RE PREGNANT,
BUT YOU'LL HAVE TO WAIT IT OUT.

45:43.809 --> 45:46.511
I'LL SEE YA. BYE-BYE.
BYE.

45:46.577 --> 45:48.847
BYE.
YOU READY TO GO HOME?

45:48.914 --> 45:51.516
[ Grunting ]

46:01.827 --> 46:04.229
ARE YOU FINDING WHAT YOU WANT?

46:04.295 --> 46:06.998
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
THEY'RE TALKIN' ABOUT.

46:07.065 --> 46:09.100
I HAVE TO LOOK UP
EVERY OTHER WORD
IN THE DICTIONARY,

46:09.167 --> 46:11.602
THEN I HAVE TO
LOOK UP THOSE WORDS IN
THE CHILDREN'S DICTIONARY.

46:11.669 --> 46:14.672
TAKES ME A HALF-HOUR
TO READ A PAGE.

46:14.739 --> 46:17.042
WELL, MAYBE THIS IS
SOMETHING THAT'S
HARD TO LEARN FROM BOOKS.

46:17.108 --> 46:20.846
I MEAN, IT'S PHOTOGRAPHY.
HARD FOR ME ANYWAY.

46:22.647 --> 46:25.016
UH--
IS SOMETHING WRONG?

46:25.083 --> 46:28.253
IS THERE A LADIES' ROOM?
YEAH.

46:46.471 --> 46:51.142
[ Novalee Shouting ]
YES! THANK YOU, LORD!
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

46:55.713 --> 46:59.150
- THINGS WENT WELL?
- YOU BET.

47:02.453 --> 47:04.322
OH, I-I GOTTA GO.

47:04.389 --> 47:07.625
OH, YOU'VE GOT A BIG DATE
OR SOMETHING?
NO.

47:07.692 --> 47:11.596
OH, BECAUSE I THOUGHT YOU WERE
SORT OF SEEING SOMEBODY, OR--

47:11.662 --> 47:16.034
NO, THAT'S DONE.
THAT'S FINISHED.
I AM DONE WITH GUYS LIKE THAT.

47:16.101 --> 47:19.304
LIKE WHAT?
YOU KNOW--
GOOD-LOOKIN', COCKY,

47:19.370 --> 47:23.141
LOOK GREAT IN TIGHT JEANS
AND A WHITE T-SHIRT.

47:23.208 --> 47:25.476
THOSE GUYS ARE
ALL WRONG FOR ME, FORNEY.

47:25.543 --> 47:28.613
I DON'T WANT THAT ANYMORE.
I WANT A CHANGE.

47:28.679 --> 47:32.683
- NO MORE MEN AT ALL.
- OH.

47:32.750 --> 47:36.187
[ Crashing ]

47:43.794 --> 47:45.997
FORNEY, HELP ME.

47:50.268 --> 47:52.803
[ Sighs ]
ALL RIGHT. HERE.

47:52.870 --> 47:54.940
OKAY.

48:03.414 --> 48:05.283
WHO'S THAT?

48:10.055 --> 48:13.558
NOVALEE, I'D LIKE YOU
TO MEET MY SISTER.

48:13.624 --> 48:15.893
THIS IS
MARY ELIZABETH HULL.

48:15.961 --> 48:17.996
SHE'S THE LIBRARIAN.

48:23.168 --> 48:25.503
MARY ELIZABETH'S
A LOT OLDER THAN I AM.

48:25.570 --> 48:27.973
I WAS STILL JUST A KID
WHEN SHE STARTED DRINKING.

48:29.074 --> 48:31.943
OH, YOU'RE UNDERSELLING THAT.
[ Chuckles ]

48:33.611 --> 48:37.115
I WAS ABOUT TEN, I GUESS,
THE FIRST TIME MY FATHER
PUT HER AWAY.

48:37.182 --> 48:41.186
AWAY? WHERE?
IN A SANITORIUM BACK EAST.

48:41.252 --> 48:45.023
SO, WHAT EXACTLY
ARE YOU LOOKING FOR?

48:45.090 --> 48:48.159
WELL, I'M LOOKIN' FOR A GIFT
FOR SISTER AND MR. SPROCK.

48:48.226 --> 48:50.328
IT'S THEIR ANNIVERSARY.
ANNIVERSARY?

48:50.395 --> 48:53.698
YEAH, THEY'VE BEEN...
CLOSE FOR SIX YEARS.

48:56.667 --> 48:59.204
SO ANYWAY, I WAS BACK EAST
AT COLLEGE, AND--

48:59.270 --> 49:01.772
COLLEGE?
YEAH, I WAS STUDYING
TO BE A HISTORY TEACHER,

49:01.839 --> 49:04.809
BUT MY DAD DIED AND MY SISTER
COULDN'T BE LEFT ALONE HERE.

49:04.875 --> 49:09.814
SHE BEGGED ME NEVER TO SEND
HER AWAY AGAIN. TOLD ME
SHE'D KILL HERSELF IF I DID.

49:09.880 --> 49:13.518
THAT WAS NINE YEARS AGO.

49:13.584 --> 49:16.054
SO WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?
CANDLESTICK HOLDERS?

49:16.121 --> 49:18.189
PICTURE FRAME?

49:18.256 --> 49:21.026
GOOD GOD. WHO WOULD BUY
SOMEBODY ELSE'S TOUPEE?

49:21.092 --> 49:25.997
[ Laughs ]
OH, MY GOSH. LOOK AT THIS.

49:26.064 --> 49:28.566
[ Blows ]

49:28.633 --> 49:31.036
IT JUST NEEDS
A LITTLE CLEANIN' IS ALL.

49:45.116 --> 49:47.118
HEY, MOSES, YOU WANT
TO HEAR SOMETHIN' FUNNY?

49:48.586 --> 49:51.189
I WOULDN'T MIND.

49:51.256 --> 49:55.226
WELL, I WAS THINKIN' THAT...

49:55.293 --> 49:57.662
SOMEDAY-- I MEAN, I MEAN
A LONG TIME FROM NOW--

49:57.728 --> 50:01.499
I COULD, YOU KNOW,
MAYBE BE A PHOTOGRAPHER.

50:01.566 --> 50:03.601
THAT'S NOT FUNNY.

50:03.668 --> 50:06.271
- IT'S NOT?
- YOU DON'T HEAR ME LAUGHIN'.

50:08.806 --> 50:11.642
** [ Rock & Roll ]

50:23.954 --> 50:26.491
[ Chattering ]

50:39.937 --> 50:43.541
** [ "Jingle Bells" Playing
On Sound System ]

50:45.476 --> 50:48.513
I NEVER HAD
A CHRISTMAS TREE BEFORE.

50:48.579 --> 50:50.381
NOT A LIVE ONE.

50:50.448 --> 50:52.983
YOU HAVE ONE OF THOSE
ALUMINUM ONES?

50:53.050 --> 50:55.153
NO.

50:56.221 --> 50:58.256
THOSE COST MONEY.

50:59.690 --> 51:02.460
NO, WHEN I WAS EIGHT,

51:02.527 --> 51:04.562
I WAS LIVIN' WITH THIS--
THIS OLD LADY.

51:04.629 --> 51:08.499
SHE PROMISED ME
WE'D HAVE A CHRISTMAS TREE.

51:08.566 --> 51:11.969
AND THEN SHE WENT
AND SPENT ALL HER MONEY...

51:12.036 --> 51:14.272
ON A SET OF BAGPIPES...

51:14.339 --> 51:19.110
BECAUSE, WELL, I GUESS
SHE WAS JUST INSANE, BUT--

51:19.177 --> 51:22.580
[ Chuckles ]
SHE, SHE FELT BAD.

51:22.647 --> 51:26.417
SO, ON CHRISTMAS MORNING,
SHE FOUND SOME GREEN PAINT,

51:26.484 --> 51:29.454
AND SHE PAINTED
A CHRISTMAS TREE...

51:29.520 --> 51:33.524
ON HER LIVING ROOM WALL,
FLOOR TO CEILIN'.

51:33.591 --> 51:37.128
AND THAT WAS MY ONLY TREE
TILL NOW.

51:40.931 --> 51:42.833
HEY.
HEY, LEXIE.

51:44.869 --> 51:46.937
HI.
HI.

51:47.004 --> 51:49.307
HEY, LEX. HI, KIDS.
[ Lexie ]
HI.

51:49.374 --> 51:52.210
HI.
EVERYBODY SAY "HI."

51:54.379 --> 51:57.815
- HOW DO YOU FEEL?
- HA! MUMPS?

51:57.882 --> 51:59.750
I GOT HIS MUMPS RIGHT HERE.

51:59.817 --> 52:02.420
ALL RIGHT, BABIES.
GO FIND US A GOOD-LOOKIN'
CHRISTMAS TREE.

52:02.487 --> 52:04.522
ONE THAT DOESN'T COST MORE
THAN $40.

52:04.589 --> 52:07.225
-SO HAVE YOU HEARD FROM HIM?
-OH, YOU MEAN, SINCE HE STOLE...

52:07.292 --> 52:11.262
MY BRAND NEW DUTCH OVEN,
KING-SIZE PILLOWS AND RODE
OUT OF TOWN ON HIS HARLEY?

52:11.329 --> 52:13.664
I GUESS THAT'S WHAT I MEANT.

52:15.333 --> 52:17.268
YOU WANT US TO WAIT AROUND,
GIVE YOU A RIDE?

52:17.335 --> 52:19.537
NAH. YOU NEVER KNOW.

52:19.604 --> 52:22.207
MAYBE I CAN GET KNOCKED UP AGAIN
ON THE WAY HOME.

52:23.241 --> 52:25.410
- MERRY CHRISTMAS.
- MERRY CHRISTMAS.

52:33.684 --> 52:36.687
WHY WOULD A MAN ON A HARLEY
STEAL A WOMAN'S PILLOWS?

52:39.023 --> 52:41.759
JUST BECAUSE HE COULD,
I GUESS.

52:53.471 --> 52:58.509
YOU KNOW, I CANNOT WAIT
TILL AMERICUS SEES THIS TREE.

52:59.610 --> 53:01.912
WELL, DON'T EXPECT TOO MUCH
OF A REACTION.

53:01.979 --> 53:04.549
AFTER ALL,
AMERICUS IS ONLY--

53:04.615 --> 53:07.318
HEY, YOU KNOW WHAT?
WHAT?

53:07.385 --> 53:11.289
AMERICUS IS EXACTLY
FIVE MONTHS OLD TODAY.

53:11.356 --> 53:14.292
WHAT?
YEAH, SHE WAS BORN JULY 5.

53:14.359 --> 53:16.394
[ Tires Screeching ]

53:29.774 --> 53:31.809
[ Sister ]
NOVALEE!
WHAT HAPPENED?

53:31.876 --> 53:34.945
I'M SORRY.
I NO MORE THAN TURNED AROUND
AND SHE WAS GONE.

53:35.012 --> 53:37.748
WHAT HAPPENED?
SHE'S GONE.
AMERICUS IS GONE.

53:37.815 --> 53:39.917
YOU SAY THE FRONT DOOR
WAS UNLOCKED.

53:39.984 --> 53:43.254
I WENT TO THE SHED
FOR MORE CHRISTMAS DECORATIONS.
I WASN'T GONE TWO MINUTES.

53:43.321 --> 53:45.256
WAS ANYTHING ELSE MISSING?
MONEY, JEWELRY?

53:45.323 --> 53:50.261
IS THERE ANYONE
YOU CAN THINK OF? ANYONE MAD
AT YOU, HAS A SCORE TO SETTLE?

53:50.328 --> 53:52.763
THERE'S A WOMAN AT WORK
DOESN'T LIKE ME MUCH.

53:52.830 --> 53:56.267
SHE SAYS I PARK IN HER SPACE
EVEN THOUGH WE DON'T HAVE
REGULAR SPACES,

53:56.334 --> 53:58.536
BUT I DON'T THINK
SHE'D TAKE AMERICUS.

53:58.603 --> 54:00.905
WHAT ABOUT YOU, SISTER?

54:00.971 --> 54:03.274
ANYONE HAVE A GRUDGE
AGAINST YOU?
LIKE WHO?

54:03.341 --> 54:07.378
SOMEONE AT THE A.A.
ANYONE THERE MIGHT WANNA
HURT YOU FOR SOME REASON?

54:07.445 --> 54:09.680
HARRY, WE'RE ALCOHOLICS.

54:09.747 --> 54:11.982
WE'RE GENERALLY SATISFIED
JUST TO HURT OURSELVES.

54:12.049 --> 54:14.785
YEAH.

54:21.125 --> 54:25.463
ANYONE COULD HAVE HER, AND
I DON'T KNOW IF SHE'S SCARED OR
IF SHE'S SICK OR IF SHE'S HURT.

54:25.530 --> 54:27.732
I DON'T KNOW
IF SHE'S HUNGRY OR COLD.

54:27.798 --> 54:29.767
I KNOW, HONEY.
I KNOW.
I DON'T EVEN--

54:29.834 --> 54:33.404
EXCUSE ME. IS THIS ALWAYS
IN THE BABY'S CRIB?

54:33.471 --> 54:36.006
NO, THAT'S NOT MY BIBLE.

54:36.073 --> 54:38.343
OH, LORD.

54:38.409 --> 54:40.711
LORD, I KNOW WHO TOOK HER.
I KNOW WHO TOOK AMERICUS.

54:40.778 --> 54:42.212
WHAT?

54:42.279 --> 54:45.049
YESTERDAY,

54:45.115 --> 54:47.318
THIS WOMAN CAME TO THE DOOR.

54:47.385 --> 54:50.788
SHE WAS HERE ONCE BEFORE.
SHE HAD A MAN WITH HER,

54:50.855 --> 54:54.592
AND THEY SAID THAT THEY WANTED
TO GIVE YOU THE WORD OF GOD.

54:56.961 --> 54:58.929
I SMART-MOUTHED 'EM,

54:58.996 --> 55:01.031
AND THEY HAD BIBLES WITH 'EM,

55:01.098 --> 55:03.100
LIKE THAT ONE.

55:03.167 --> 55:05.035
THEY CAME FROM MISSISSIPPI--

55:05.102 --> 55:07.538
MIDNIGHT, MISSISSIPPI.

55:10.341 --> 55:12.943
THEY SAID MY BABY
WAS AN ABOMINATION?

55:16.581 --> 55:19.216
AM I BEIN' PUNISHED, FORNEY?

55:19.283 --> 55:20.785
FOR WHAT?

55:20.851 --> 55:22.787
THINGS I DID.

55:24.489 --> 55:26.891
I WASN'T MARRIED
WHEN I HAD MY BABY.

55:28.893 --> 55:31.429
DO YOU REALLY THINK
THIS IS WHAT YOU DESERVE?

55:33.698 --> 55:36.066
LET ME TELL YOU ABOUT
WHAT YOU DESERVE, NOVALEE.

55:36.133 --> 55:39.670
- IF IT WERE UP TO ME--
- [ Siren Wailing ]

55:45.676 --> 55:49.046
[ Wailing Continues ]

55:54.084 --> 55:56.821
[ Truck Doors Close ]
[ Engine Starts ]

55:58.088 --> 56:01.025
[ Dispatcher, Indistinct ]

56:03.994 --> 56:07.331
SORRY, FOLKS.
WE GOT A CLASSICAL CRIME SCENE
ACROSS THE STREET.

56:07.398 --> 56:09.434
OH, MY GOD!
YOU CAN'T--
LET HER GO!

56:09.500 --> 56:12.403
HEY, HEY, HEY!
GET DOWN!

56:12.470 --> 56:15.139
HEY!
[ Sirens Wailing ]

56:15.205 --> 56:17.708
[ Tires Screech ]

56:19.043 --> 56:22.413
[ Gasping ]

56:22.480 --> 56:24.582
[ Sirens Stop ]

56:38.228 --> 56:40.097
[ Baby Fussing ]

56:45.970 --> 56:49.440
[ Crying ]

56:49.507 --> 56:51.809
[ Laughing ]

56:51.876 --> 56:56.080
A HIGHWAY PATROL
HAD SPOTTED A MISSISSIPPI PLATE
AND STOPPED 'EM.

56:56.146 --> 56:59.550
THEY ADMITTED THEY TOOK HER AND
SAID WE'D FIND HER RIGHT HERE.

56:59.617 --> 57:02.753
[ Continues Crying ]

57:25.009 --> 57:29.580
JESUS CHRIST.
ANOTHER GUITAR PLAYER.
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

57:29.647 --> 57:31.716
WILLY JACK PICKENS.

57:31.782 --> 57:34.985
YOU DIDN'T EVEN
HAVE TO MAKE THAT UP DID YOU?

57:35.052 --> 57:36.320
WHAT?

57:36.386 --> 57:39.156
WELL, YOU JUST CARRY THAT GUITAR
AROUND TO KEEP YOUR BALANCE?

57:39.223 --> 57:41.325
YOU WANT ME TO PLAY?

57:41.391 --> 57:44.194
WHAT THE FUCK DO YOU THINK
I WANT YOU TO DO, CALL BINGO?

57:46.330 --> 57:49.800
ONE, TWO. YOU'RE BEST SHOT.

57:49.867 --> 57:52.937
ALL RIGHT.
WELL, I WROTE THIS ONE MYSELF.

57:53.003 --> 57:57.074
- I HAVE GOOSE BUMPS ALREADY.
- JESUS CHRIST.

57:57.141 --> 58:01.846
** [ Guitar ]

58:03.480 --> 58:05.683
* SOMETIMES IT'S HARD *

58:05.750 --> 58:09.820
* YOU DON'T WANNA LOOK
OVER YOUR SHOULDER *

58:10.855 --> 58:13.357
* 'CAUSE YOU DON'T WANT TO *

58:13.423 --> 58:16.093
* REMEMBER WHERE YOU'VE BEEN *

58:17.595 --> 58:19.830
* THERE'LL COME A TIME
YOU'D DIE *

58:19.897 --> 58:24.234
* IF YOU COULD ONLY HOLD HER *

58:24.301 --> 58:29.774
* I KNOW THAT'S WHERE I AM *

58:32.342 --> 58:34.645
* SO LISTEN
WITH ALL YOUR HEART *

58:34.712 --> 58:39.083
* HOLD IT INSIDE FOREVER *

58:39.149 --> 58:43.320
* YOU MAY FIND ALL YOUR DREAMS
HAVE ALREADY *

58:43.387 --> 58:45.823
* COME TRUE *

58:45.890 --> 58:48.192
* LOOK INSIDE
AND FIND THE PART *

58:48.258 --> 58:52.563
* THAT'S LEADING YOU *

58:52.630 --> 58:56.901
* THAT'S THE BEAT
OF THE HEART **

59:00.805 --> 59:02.873
** [ Guitar Stops ]

59:06.443 --> 59:08.478
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

59:08.545 --> 59:11.415
IT'S GONNA COST ME
$1,000 TO CLEAN YOU UP.

59:11.481 --> 59:14.685
PICTURES, ANOTHER 200.

59:16.621 --> 59:19.824
MY NAME'S RUTH MEYERS.
CALL ME RUTH MEYERS.

59:20.825 --> 59:23.493
ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.

59:23.560 --> 59:25.429
[ Hair Dryer Whirring ]

59:25.495 --> 59:28.633
WELL, PENNY,
COULD YOU JUST PLEASE SIGN IT?
THANK YOU.

59:28.699 --> 59:31.001
BY THE WAY,
I CHANGED YOUR NAME.

59:31.068 --> 59:33.503
YOU DID?
YES, YOU'RE BILLY SHADOW NOW.

59:33.570 --> 59:35.572
ONE WILLY IN THE BUSINESS
IS ENOUGH.

59:35.640 --> 59:38.142
BILLY SHADOW.
I LIKE IT.

59:38.208 --> 59:39.977
HERE.

59:41.411 --> 59:43.914
SPENDING MONEY?

59:46.817 --> 59:49.286
** [ Country Rock ]

59:51.722 --> 59:54.925
* SO LISTEN
WITH ALL YOUR HEART *

59:54.992 --> 59:57.862
* HOLD IT INSIDE FOREVER *
[ Glass Shattering ]

59:57.928 --> 01:00:03.167
- [ Grunting ]
- * YOU MAY FIND ALL YOUR DREAMS
HAVE ALREADY COME TRUE *

01:00:05.269 --> 01:00:09.073
- [ Grunts ]
- WHOA!

01:00:09.139 --> 01:00:11.341
[ Ruth ]
I TOLD YOU
IT WASN'T GONNA BE EASY.

01:00:11.408 --> 01:00:13.911
I TOLD YOU IT WOULD TAKE TWO
YEARS TO GET YOU ON THE RADIO.

01:00:13.978 --> 01:00:17.114
BUT IT'S BEEN TWO YEARS.
WELL, THEN YOU KNOW WHAT?

01:00:17.181 --> 01:00:21.285
WHAT?
IT'S GONNA TAKE THREE YEARS.

01:00:21.351 --> 01:00:23.120
[ Line Disconnects ]

01:00:25.622 --> 01:00:28.058
* YOU MAY FIND ALL YOUR DREAMS *

01:00:28.125 --> 01:00:32.029
* HAVE ALREADY COME TRUE *

01:00:33.163 --> 01:00:35.532
* LOOK INSIDE
AND FIND THE PART *

01:00:35.599 --> 01:00:39.636
* THAT'S LEADIN' YOU *

01:00:41.105 --> 01:00:46.677
* THAT'S THE BEAT OF THE HEART *

01:00:48.312 --> 01:00:50.614
* NO ONE *

01:00:50.681 --> 01:00:54.018
* CAN TELL YOU
HOW TO GET THERE *

01:00:54.084 --> 01:00:56.453
* IT'S A ROAD YOU TAKE *

01:00:56.520 --> 01:00:59.957
* ALL BY YOURSELF *
COME ON, AMERICUS.
SING WITH ME.

01:01:00.024 --> 01:01:05.662
* ALL BY YOURSELF *
* ALL BY YOURSELF *

01:01:05.730 --> 01:01:07.531
OH, THAT SONG!

01:01:07.597 --> 01:01:10.067
* ALL YOUR HEART *

01:01:10.134 --> 01:01:12.436
* HOLD IT IN-- **
[ Radio Stops ]

01:01:12.502 --> 01:01:14.338
- IT'S CATCHY.
- I DON'T KNOW.

01:01:14.404 --> 01:01:18.208
SOMETHING ABOUT THAT GUY'S VOICE
JUST RUBS ME THE WRONG WAY.

01:01:20.745 --> 01:01:23.413
AMERICUS, HONEY,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

01:01:23.480 --> 01:01:26.884
EATIN' DOUGH IN MY NOSE.
DON'T.

01:01:26.951 --> 01:01:28.786
FORNEY'S OUTSIDE WAITIN'.

01:01:28.853 --> 01:01:31.221
[ Giggling ]

01:01:32.589 --> 01:01:34.591
HOW DO I LOOK?

01:01:34.658 --> 01:01:38.028
GREAT. HOW DO I LOOK?
NERVOUS?

01:01:38.095 --> 01:01:40.030
UH-HUH.

01:01:42.099 --> 01:01:44.568
[ Forney ]
ARE YOU READY TO GO?
FORNEY!

01:01:44.634 --> 01:01:46.603
OH!
PONY RIDE!

01:01:46.670 --> 01:01:48.538
WELL, IF IT DOESN'T RAIN.

01:01:48.605 --> 01:01:50.640
IT CAN'T RAIN.

01:01:50.707 --> 01:01:52.943
I'M SHOOTIN'
AN OUTDOOR WEDDING.

01:02:00.517 --> 01:02:02.286
DO I LOOK PROFESSIONAL?

01:02:02.352 --> 01:02:05.055
- YOU KNOW WHAT WOULD HELP?
- WHAT?

01:02:05.122 --> 01:02:06.791
IF YOU BROUGHT YOUR CAMERA.

01:02:06.857 --> 01:02:09.393
SHIT.
MAMA DIDN'T SAY, "SHIT."

01:02:09.459 --> 01:02:11.862
YES YOU DID.
HERE YOU GO.

01:02:11.929 --> 01:02:15.632
NOW YOU TAKE SOME BEAUTIFUL
PICTURE OF THAT WEDDIN'.
YOU LOOK WONDERFUL.

01:02:15.699 --> 01:02:17.768
DRIVE CAREFUL, ALL RIGHT?
BYE, BABY.

01:02:17.835 --> 01:02:19.804
BYE.
BYE. GOOD LUCK.

01:02:19.870 --> 01:02:22.039
SAY BYE TO MAMA. BYE.
BYE.

01:02:22.106 --> 01:02:24.041
[ Americus ]
BYE. BYE, MAMA.
[ Sister ] GOOD LUCK.

01:02:24.108 --> 01:02:26.110
[ Forney ]
BYE.
BYE.

01:02:29.914 --> 01:02:32.282
[ Wind Blowing ]

01:02:37.988 --> 01:02:40.490
MOMMY! MOMMY!
STORM'S COMIN'!

01:02:40.557 --> 01:02:45.195
WEATHER CHANNEL
JUST PUT OUT A TORNADO WARNIN'.
WE BETTER GET GOING.

01:02:50.134 --> 01:02:53.037
OOH. YOU BETTER
PICK THESE UP.

01:02:53.103 --> 01:02:55.739
HERE YOU GO.
I SWEAR.

01:02:55.806 --> 01:02:58.008
I SPENT MORE ON FILM
THAN I GOT PAID.

01:02:58.075 --> 01:03:00.110
WHAT IS GOIN' ON HERE?

01:03:00.177 --> 01:03:03.713
WELL, IT TURNS OUT THAT
THE GROOM'S FORMER GIRLFRIEND...

01:03:03.780 --> 01:03:05.782
WAS A WAITRESS
AT THE RECEPTION.

01:03:05.850 --> 01:03:09.854
AND THIS WAS RIGHT AFTER
THE BRIDE CALLED HER
A CHEAP, BIG-ASS TRAMP.

01:03:09.920 --> 01:03:12.556
OOH. WHO'S THIS
ON THE STRETCHER?

01:03:12.622 --> 01:03:15.826
THAT'S THE WAITRESS AFTER
THE BRIDESMAIDS FINISHED
JUMPIN' UP AND DOWN ON HER.

01:03:15.893 --> 01:03:19.329
[ Both Laughing ]
YOU THINK THEY'RE GONNA
WANT THESE PICTURES?

01:03:19.396 --> 01:03:23.133
I TOOK EVERYTHING.
OOH, WE BETTER GET MOVIN'.

01:03:23.200 --> 01:03:25.769
I'LL MEET YOU TWO
IN THE CELLAR.

01:03:25.836 --> 01:03:27.872
I'M READY!

01:03:27.938 --> 01:03:30.841
YOU CERTAINLY ARE.
NOW, YOU'RE ALL SET.

01:03:30.908 --> 01:03:32.843
GOT IT?

01:03:32.910 --> 01:03:34.845
WHERE YOU GOIN'?

01:03:34.912 --> 01:03:38.815
DIXIE MARLON'S STILL SICK.
GONNA BRING HER SOME POTATO SOUP
RIGHT QUICK.

01:03:38.883 --> 01:03:40.817
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

01:03:40.885 --> 01:03:43.320
[ Wind Gusting ]

01:03:46.690 --> 01:03:48.825
[ Dog Barking ]

01:03:51.962 --> 01:03:53.898
[ Phone Ringing ]
PICK IT UP.
PICK IT UP.

01:03:53.964 --> 01:03:56.000
COME ON, NOVALEE,
PICK IT UP. PICK IT UP.

01:03:56.066 --> 01:03:59.536
[ Ringing ]
[ TV ] THOSE IN ROGERS COUNTY
SHOULD TAKE ACTION AS WELL.

01:03:59.603 --> 01:04:02.339
THIS INCLUDES AREAS
OF CLAREMORE AND SEQUOYAH.
[ Ringing Continues ]

01:04:02.406 --> 01:04:05.042
[ Moans ]
[ Softly ]
ALL RIGHT.

01:04:05.109 --> 01:04:07.144
OH.
I GOT YOU.

01:04:08.845 --> 01:04:10.814
ROSITA, HELP ME.

01:04:10.881 --> 01:04:15.619
[ Americus ] I'M SCARED.
I'VE GOT YOU, HONEY.
HOLD ON. I'VE GOT YOU.

01:04:15.685 --> 01:04:18.488
[ Radio Announcer ]
WE INTERRUPT THIS PROGRAM FOR
AN IMPORTANT WEATHER BULLETIN.

01:04:18.555 --> 01:04:20.157
WHERE'S GRANDMA SISTER?

01:04:20.224 --> 01:04:23.027
SHE'S COMING, HONEY,
ALL RIGHT?

01:04:23.093 --> 01:04:26.163
- THERE YOU GO.
- [ Radio ] THOSE OF YOU
IN ROGERS COUNTY--

01:04:26.230 --> 01:04:29.033
MY HUSBAND'S PAINTING A HOUSE
SOMEWHERE ON COMMERCE STREET.

01:04:29.099 --> 01:04:31.801
HE'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

01:04:31.868 --> 01:04:35.772
HI, AMERICUS.
DO YOU WANNA PLAY CARDS?
I WANNA PLAY WITH MY BEAR.

01:04:35.839 --> 01:04:40.344
[ Americus ]
HE'S SCARED OF THE STORM.
I'M GONNA GO LOOK FOR SISTER.

01:04:40.410 --> 01:04:42.279
SISTER?

01:04:48.652 --> 01:04:51.388
SHOULDN'T WE SHUT THE DOOR?

01:04:51.455 --> 01:04:53.690
SISTER'S STILL COMIN'.
LET'S WAIT.

01:04:53.757 --> 01:04:56.360
[ Siren Wailing ]

01:04:59.529 --> 01:05:01.398
OH, GOD.

01:05:03.067 --> 01:05:05.435
NOVALEE, COME BACK.
MOMMY,
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

01:05:05.502 --> 01:05:07.337
NOVALEE, PLEASE!

01:05:20.384 --> 01:05:22.652
[ Grunts ]

01:05:22.719 --> 01:05:25.055
[ Grunting Continues ]

01:05:35.599 --> 01:05:38.235
[ Screaming ]
MOMMY!

01:05:38.302 --> 01:05:41.538
[ Rosita ]
COME HERE! COME HERE!

01:05:41.605 --> 01:05:44.941
[ Screaming Continues ]

01:05:45.009 --> 01:05:47.244
AMERICUS, COME HERE!

01:05:48.778 --> 01:05:50.880
[ Screaming Continues ]

01:05:50.947 --> 01:05:53.083
HOLD ON, NOVALEE!
I'VE GOT YOU!

01:05:53.150 --> 01:05:56.386
- STAY HERE, AMERICUS!
- AMERICUS, STAY BACK!

01:05:56.453 --> 01:05:58.155
KIDS, GET BACK!

01:06:04.094 --> 01:06:06.930
- AMERICUS!
- HANG ON!

01:06:06.997 --> 01:06:10.300
- GET BACK, BABY!
- AMERICUS, NO!

01:06:11.468 --> 01:06:14.404
[ Whimpering ]

01:06:14.471 --> 01:06:17.041
- NO!
- MOMMY!

01:06:55.145 --> 01:06:57.214
[ Shutter Clicking ]

01:07:06.856 --> 01:07:08.758
LOOK, MOMMY.

01:07:53.069 --> 01:07:56.106
[ Lexie ] I STILL DON'T KNOW
WHY THEY COULDN'T REOPEN
THE WAL-MART HERE.

01:07:56.173 --> 01:08:00.009
TOO MUCH STRUCTURAL DAMAGE.
WELL, LIVIN' IN POTEAU,
WE'LL NEVER SEE YOU.

01:08:00.076 --> 01:08:02.612
THAT'S WHERE
THEY BUILT THE NEW STORE.
I GOTTA GO, LEXIE.

01:08:02.679 --> 01:08:05.715
WHAT ELSE CAN I DO?
I'VE GOTTA MAKE A LIVING.

01:08:05.782 --> 01:08:09.119
SO WHERE'S THIS GUY
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO MEET?
COME ON, HONEY.

01:08:10.053 --> 01:08:12.322
WHERE IS HE?

01:08:12.389 --> 01:08:16.593
WE'RE STILL EARLY.
MOMMY, CAN I PLAY?

01:08:16.660 --> 01:08:20.397
YEAH, YOU CAN PLAY
FOR A COUPLE OF MINUTES, HONEY,
BUT THEN WE HAVE TO GO.

01:08:24.334 --> 01:08:26.736
A TRAILER.
HMM?

01:08:26.803 --> 01:08:31.441
THE PLACE I RENTED IN POTEAU.
IT'S GOT WHEELS UNDER IT.

01:08:31.508 --> 01:08:34.743
- FORNEY CALLED ME LAST NIGHT.
- FORNEY?

01:08:34.810 --> 01:08:37.680
I FIGURED HIS SISTER
FELL OUT A WINDOW OR SOMETHIN'.

01:08:37.747 --> 01:08:40.417
HE ASKED ME IF I COULD FIND YOU
A JOB AT THE HOSPITAL,
AND I SAID,

01:08:40.484 --> 01:08:43.220
"OH, GEE, FORNEY, AS WHAT,
BRAIN SURGEON ON WEEKENDS?"

01:08:43.287 --> 01:08:47.055
- [ Chuckles ]
- THAT BOY DOES NOT
WANT YOU TO MOVE TO POTEAU.

01:08:47.122 --> 01:08:50.894
IT'S JUST HE'S SO CRAZY
ABOUT AMERICUS.

01:08:50.960 --> 01:08:52.962
OH, GIVE ME A BREAK.

01:08:53.029 --> 01:08:56.899
HE IS.
FORNEY IS IN LOVE WITH YOU.

01:08:56.966 --> 01:08:58.868
TELL ME
YOU DON'T KNOW THAT.

01:09:00.203 --> 01:09:02.506
IT'S JUST NOT LIKE THAT
WITH ME AND FORNEY.

01:09:02.572 --> 01:09:06.443
I HAVE SEEN HIM.
HE LOVES YOU.

01:09:06.510 --> 01:09:09.513
HE LOVES THE WAY YOU WALK.
HE LOVES YOUR HAIR.

01:09:09.578 --> 01:09:12.182
HE LOVES EVERYTHING
ABOUT YOU.

01:09:12.249 --> 01:09:16.185
FORNEY AND ME--
WE'RE JUST NOT THAT WAY.

01:09:16.252 --> 01:09:18.488
FORNEY'S DIFFERENT FROM US.

01:09:18.555 --> 01:09:21.358
HE WENT TO COLLEGE.
HIS FAMILY HAD MONEY.

01:09:21.425 --> 01:09:23.627
WHAT ARE YOU TRYIN' TO SAY,

01:09:23.693 --> 01:09:25.895
THAT YOU'RE NOT GOOD ENOUGH
FOR HIM?

01:09:28.198 --> 01:09:30.234
[ Horn Honks ]

01:09:31.268 --> 01:09:33.270
I WONDER WHAT HE WANTS.

01:09:33.337 --> 01:09:36.573
I WOULDN'T KNOW.
HE JUST CALLED ME LAST NIGHT
AND ASKED TO MEET ME.

01:09:36.640 --> 01:09:39.709
AND I TOLD HIM
I WAS GOIN' OUT OF TOWN,
BUT HE STILL WANTED TO.

01:09:43.313 --> 01:09:46.283
- MISS NATION.
- UH-UH. HER.

01:09:46.350 --> 01:09:48.652
HI. I'M RAY.
HI.

01:09:48.718 --> 01:09:51.488
WELL, SISTER SPOKE OF YOU OFTEN
AT THE MEETINGS.

01:09:51.555 --> 01:09:55.058
- OH, BOTH OF YOU WERE AL--
- ALCOHOLICS, YES, MA'AM.

01:09:55.124 --> 01:09:58.662
- RAY? YOU USED TO CALL IN--
- CALL IN THE MIDDLE
OF THE NIGHT.

01:09:58.728 --> 01:10:03.032
AND SISTER WOULD COME
AND PICK MY SORRY ASS UP--
EXCUSE ME--

01:10:03.099 --> 01:10:06.703
IN WHATEVER SLEAZY BEER JOINT
I HAPPENED TO BE PASSED OUT IN.

01:10:06.770 --> 01:10:10.907
[ Sighs ]
SHE NEVER GAVE UP ON ME,
EVEN AFTER I GOT DISBARRED.

01:10:12.509 --> 01:10:17.381
YOU KNOW, I ONCE WENT
INTO COURT AND STARTED
DEFENDIN' THE WRONG PERSON.

01:10:17.447 --> 01:10:19.983
[ Laughing ]
ANYWAY,

01:10:20.049 --> 01:10:22.819
SHE'S THE ONE WHO HELPED ME
TURN IT ALL AROUND--

01:10:22.886 --> 01:10:24.721
GET MY LICENSE BACK.

01:10:26.756 --> 01:10:29.659
- WELL, EVERYTHING'S IN HERE.
- WHAT IS?

01:10:29.726 --> 01:10:32.496
IT'S SISTER'S ESTATE.
ESTATE?

01:10:32.562 --> 01:10:34.931
YEAH, SHE LEFT IT ALL TO YOU.

01:10:34.998 --> 01:10:40.437
THE LAND, THE INSURANCE
ON THE TRAILER AND CONTENTS,
LIFE INSURANCE,

01:10:40.504 --> 01:10:46.109
EVEN SOME OLD OIL STOCK
HER GRANDFATHER BOUGHT FROM
THE COMANCHES BACK IN 1909.

01:10:46.175 --> 01:10:49.045
- COMES TO ABOUT $41,000.
- [ Gasps ]

01:10:49.112 --> 01:10:52.382
[ Spits ]
SORRY.

01:10:52.449 --> 01:10:55.419
[ Chuckling ]

01:10:56.753 --> 01:10:58.655
* I'M GONNA SHAKE MY SOUL *

01:10:58.722 --> 01:11:00.857
* AND RELEASE MY HOLD *

01:11:00.924 --> 01:11:02.959
* GIVIN' UP CONTROL *

01:11:03.026 --> 01:11:05.028
* AND LET THE REST UNFOLD *

01:11:05.094 --> 01:11:08.332
* 'CAUSE IT'S A LONG, LONG WAY
FROM HERE *

01:11:08.398 --> 01:11:11.368
* TO WHERE WE GO *
[ Kids Shouting ]

01:11:11.435 --> 01:11:14.304
BROWNIE! BROWNIE,
DO NOT LASSO YOUR SISTER!

01:11:14.371 --> 01:11:16.706
* TAKE OFF THE TRAINING WHEELS *

01:11:16.773 --> 01:11:19.008
* LIFT OFF THE HANDLE BARS *

01:11:23.447 --> 01:11:25.582
* I'LL DRIVE RIGHT THROUGH
MY FEARS *

01:11:25.649 --> 01:11:28.352
* AND RESURRECT MY HEART *

01:11:30.687 --> 01:11:34.458
MR. SPROCK, I STILL
DON'T FEEL RIGHT ABOUT THIS.

01:11:34.524 --> 01:11:37.126
I FEEL LIKE SOME OF WHAT
SISTER HAD SHOULD BE YOURS.

01:11:37.193 --> 01:11:41.064
THE ONLY THING I WANTED I GOT--
THAT OLD KITCHEN TABLE.

01:11:42.532 --> 01:11:45.602
A LOT OF FINE MEMORIES.

01:11:45.669 --> 01:11:47.537
ALL RIGHT.

01:11:49.406 --> 01:11:51.341
* I'M GONNA SHAKE MY SOUL *

01:11:51.408 --> 01:11:54.077
* AND RELEASE MY HOLD *

01:11:54.143 --> 01:11:56.312
* I'M GIVIN' UP CONTROL *

01:11:56.380 --> 01:11:58.515
* I LET THE REST UNFOLD *

01:11:58.582 --> 01:12:00.750
* 'CAUSE IT'S
A LONG, LONG WAY *

01:12:00.817 --> 01:12:02.786
* IT'S A LONG, LONG WAY *

01:12:02.852 --> 01:12:06.823
* FROM HERE TO WHERE WE GO **

01:12:09.393 --> 01:12:12.161
** [ Blues ]

01:12:12.228 --> 01:12:15.799
I JUST THINK THAT RUTH MEYERS
HAS WENT ABOUT AS FAR AS SHE CAN
WITH ME.

01:12:15.865 --> 01:12:19.235
MY HEAD JUST KEEPS BUTTIN'
AGAINST THE CEILIN',
AND I WANNA BREAK THROUGH.

01:12:19.302 --> 01:12:22.338
AND YOU'RE THE GUY.
YOU'RE JOHNNY DESOTO,
FOR CHRIST'S SAKE.

01:12:22.406 --> 01:12:24.474
YOU GOT THE CLOUT.
WELL,

01:12:24.541 --> 01:12:29.312
I WILL SAY I THOUGHT YOU'D
PICK UP A LITTLE MORE MOMENTUM
OFF OF "BEAT OF A HEART."

01:12:29.379 --> 01:12:31.715
EXACTLY.
THAT WAS EIGHT MONTHS AGO.

01:12:31.781 --> 01:12:35.685
HERE I AM IN SANTA-FRIGGIN'-FE
STILL PLAYIN' TO DAMN CLUBS.

01:12:38.388 --> 01:12:41.691
SHIT.
I GOTTA GO GET READY.
I GOT A SHOW.

01:12:42.859 --> 01:12:48.097
YOU AND RUTH MEYERS
GOT SOME KIND OF A CONTRACT?

01:12:48.164 --> 01:12:52.569
I JUST WANNA WARN YOU.
RUTH MEYERS COULD BE
A POWERFUL ALLY,

01:12:52.636 --> 01:12:54.604
BUT SHE MAKES
A HELL OF AN ENEMY.

01:12:54.671 --> 01:12:57.306
YOU MESS WITH HER, AND
NOBODY'LL TOUCH YOU.

01:12:57.373 --> 01:13:01.945
JOHNNY, RUTH MEYERS
AIN'T GOT THAT KIND OF CLOUT.
COME ON.

01:13:20.764 --> 01:13:22.799
[ Elevator Bell Dings ]

01:13:30.106 --> 01:13:32.476
[ Applause ]

01:13:32.542 --> 01:13:36.546
AND THE WINNER OF THIS YEAR'S
KODAK FIRST PRIZE,

01:13:36.613 --> 01:13:39.082
FOR THE GREATER SOUTHWEST AREA,

01:13:39.148 --> 01:13:42.486
SHE'S FROM SEQUOYAH, OKLAHOMA.

01:13:42.552 --> 01:13:45.455
HOW 'BOUT A REAL BIG HAND
FOR MISS NOVALEE NATION?

01:13:45.522 --> 01:13:48.024
NOVALEE, CONGRATULATIONS.
WAY TO GO.

01:13:59.836 --> 01:14:03.172
I SHOT THIS PICTURE
WITH A ROLLEI TWIN LENS
REFLEX AT F-4...

01:14:03.239 --> 01:14:06.042
USING A.S.A. 125.

01:14:06.109 --> 01:14:10.547
I TOOK IT--
I TOOK IT TO REMEMBER
A VERY DEAR FRIEND.

01:14:13.550 --> 01:14:17.353
SHE GAVE ME THAT TREE,
AND THEN SHE TOOK ME IN...

01:14:17.420 --> 01:14:20.524
WHEN ME AND MY BABY HAD NO PLACE
ELSE IN THE WORLD TO GO.

01:14:22.025 --> 01:14:24.694
AND I WOULD RATHER
BE LIVIN' AGAIN WITH HER
IN THAT TRAILER...

01:14:24.761 --> 01:14:27.196
THAN IN THE FINEST HOUSE
IN OKLAHOMA.

01:14:29.365 --> 01:14:32.836
THANK YOU.
[ Applause ]

01:14:34.137 --> 01:14:36.005
[ Giggling ]

01:14:39.475 --> 01:14:42.245
ALL RIGHT. HOLD ON.
WE'RE ALMOST THERE.

01:14:52.656 --> 01:14:54.924
WHO'S THAT?
WHO'S WHAT?

01:14:54.991 --> 01:14:57.260
THERE'S A LADY.

01:15:00.263 --> 01:15:02.198
RUTH MEYERS.

01:15:02.265 --> 01:15:05.234
YOU, OUT.

01:15:05.301 --> 01:15:08.171
ARE YOU MARRIED?

01:15:08.237 --> 01:15:10.707
- TO HER?
- OUT.

01:15:10.774 --> 01:15:13.476
I WILL LEAVE
WHEN I AM GOOD AND READY.

01:15:13.543 --> 01:15:16.813
[ Grunts, Moans ]

01:15:16.880 --> 01:15:20.283
[ Door Slams ]
SO, HOW'S IT GOIN'?

01:15:20.349 --> 01:15:23.853
SO, I GOT A CALL FROM
AN ATTORNEY DOWN IN ALBUQUERQUE.

01:15:26.790 --> 01:15:28.892
WELL, HELL,
IF THIS IS ABOUT THAT GIRL--

01:15:28.958 --> 01:15:32.762
IT'S ABOUT A GUY
NAMED TOMMY REYNOLDS.

01:15:32.829 --> 01:15:35.498
- WHO?
- DON'T LIE TO ME!

01:15:35.565 --> 01:15:38.935
GOD! ALL RIGHT.
TOMMY REYNOLDS. WHAT?

01:15:39.002 --> 01:15:43.039
- HE SAYS HE WAS
YOUR CELLMATE IN PRISON.
- SO?

01:15:43.106 --> 01:15:45.508
HE SAYS HE WROTE
"BEAT OF A HEART."

01:15:45.575 --> 01:15:48.344
THAT IS SUCH BULLSHIT.

01:15:48.411 --> 01:15:52.315
I WROTE THAT SONG.
HE SOLD ME HIS DAMN GUITAR.
THAT'S IT.

01:15:52.381 --> 01:15:55.985
I GOT THE CRAP KICKED OUT OF ME
FOR WRITIN' THAT SONG.

01:16:01.591 --> 01:16:03.660
SHIT!

01:16:05.061 --> 01:16:07.563
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?
WHAT--

01:16:07.631 --> 01:16:12.802
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?
WE AIN'T GONNA DO NOTHIN'.

01:16:14.871 --> 01:16:17.907
MAYBE JOHNNY DESOTO
WILL HELP YOU OUT.

01:16:25.081 --> 01:16:27.283
[ Door Opens ]

01:16:27.350 --> 01:16:29.953
RUTH. RUTH MEYERS.

01:16:30.019 --> 01:16:32.221
COME ON.
I NEED YOUR HELP WITH THIS.
[ Elevator Bell Dings ]

01:16:33.356 --> 01:16:35.258
HEY, RUTHIE.

01:16:35.324 --> 01:16:38.261
I BET IF WE WENT BACK TO MY ROOM
WE COULD WORK IT OUT.

01:16:38.327 --> 01:16:41.397
HUH? YOU SEXY SWEET THING.

01:16:41.464 --> 01:16:44.701
[ Grunts ]
OH, GODDAMN!

01:16:57.346 --> 01:16:59.415
HI!

01:16:59.482 --> 01:17:01.384
HI, HONEY.
SORRY, BUT I MADE IT.

01:17:01.450 --> 01:17:03.319
WAS IT A BIG INCONVENIENCE?

01:17:03.386 --> 01:17:07.490
NOVALEE, I HAVE FIVE CHILDREN.
EVERYTHING IS AN INCONVENIENCE.

01:17:07.556 --> 01:17:11.627
YOU MIND IF I DRIVE REAL SLOW
ON THE WAY HOME? I'D LIKE
TO PRETEND IT'S A VACATION.

01:17:11.695 --> 01:17:13.629
YOU ALL RIGHT, HONEY?
I'M GREAT.

01:17:13.697 --> 01:17:16.900
GOOD.
SO, ANYTHING NEW AROUND HERE?

01:17:16.966 --> 01:17:19.669
NO, NOT A THING,
UNLESS YOU THINK
ME MEETIN' A GUY IS NEW.

01:17:19.736 --> 01:17:23.006
WHO? HOW?
WELL, HIS NAME IS ROGER.

01:17:23.072 --> 01:17:25.742
ROGER BRISCO.
HE'S A C.P.A.

01:17:25.809 --> 01:17:30.346
HE HAS HIS OWN SUCCESSFUL
BUSINESS IN FORT WORTH.
HOW'D YOU MEET HIM?

01:17:30.413 --> 01:17:34.050
WE PUMPED GAS
TOGETHER AT THE TEXACO.
HE DRIVES A NEW BUICK.

01:17:34.117 --> 01:17:37.954
AND WHEN HIS DIPSTICK
GOT JAMMED, I HELPED HIM
YANK IT OUT.

01:17:38.021 --> 01:17:40.089
YEAH.

01:17:40.156 --> 01:17:44.160
HE TOLD ME
MY KIDS WERE BEAUTIFUL,
SO I KNOW HE LIKES ME.

01:17:46.029 --> 01:17:48.597
YOU NEVER KNOW, NOVALEE.

01:17:48.664 --> 01:17:51.200
MAYBE IN A COUPLE OF MONTHS,
YOU'LL BE TAKIN' PICTURES
AT MY WEDDIN'.

01:17:52.401 --> 01:17:54.704
OH. ALL RIGHT. THANK YOU.

01:17:54.771 --> 01:17:56.572
YOU'RE WELCOME, HONEY.
BYE.

01:17:56.639 --> 01:17:58.541
BYE. OH.

01:17:58.607 --> 01:18:00.209
WHAT?

01:18:00.276 --> 01:18:03.412
I FORGOT TO GET FORNEY A GIFT
FOR WATCHIN' AMERICUS.

01:18:03.479 --> 01:18:05.849
- OH, I KNOW
WHAT YOU CAN GIVE HIM.
- WHAT?

01:18:07.683 --> 01:18:10.286
[ Laughing ]
OH!

01:18:11.955 --> 01:18:16.392
NO, I-I'LL GIVE HIM...
HOTEL SLIPPERS.

01:18:16.459 --> 01:18:18.995
OH, NOVALEE, THAT'S JUST
WHAT EVERY MAN WANTS.

01:18:19.062 --> 01:18:22.031
A NICE PAIR
OF HOUSE SLIPPERS.

01:18:22.098 --> 01:18:23.967
BYE.
BYE.

01:18:31.174 --> 01:18:33.042
FORNEY.

01:18:56.732 --> 01:18:58.201
[ Camera Shutter Clicks ]

01:19:06.675 --> 01:19:08.812
[ Shutter Clicks ]

01:19:10.246 --> 01:19:12.949
MMM. HI.

01:19:14.250 --> 01:19:17.286
- WHAT TIME IS IT?
- IT'S LATE. SORRY.

01:19:18.421 --> 01:19:20.857
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

01:19:20.924 --> 01:19:24.193
MM, HOW WAS YOUR TRIP?
GREAT.

01:19:26.129 --> 01:19:28.064
WELL, BETTER GET HER TO BED.

01:19:28.131 --> 01:19:30.399
NO, THAT'S OKAY.
I'LL DO IT.

01:19:35.538 --> 01:19:37.974
[ Whispering ]
HEY. THERE.

01:19:51.554 --> 01:19:53.389
FORNEY?
MM-HMM.

01:20:02.598 --> 01:20:04.500
I BROUGHT THESE FOR YOU.

01:20:04.567 --> 01:20:07.436
OH! THANKS.

01:20:12.842 --> 01:20:15.344
- BYE.
- GOOD NIGHT.

01:20:35.865 --> 01:20:37.566
[ Phone Ringing ]

01:20:39.735 --> 01:20:41.837
HELLO?

01:20:42.906 --> 01:20:45.308
HELLO?
IS SOMEBODY THERE?

01:20:45.374 --> 01:20:47.276
WHO?

01:20:48.811 --> 01:20:50.914
BROWNIE?

01:20:51.847 --> 01:20:54.050
WHY? WHERE'S LEXIE?

01:20:55.051 --> 01:20:58.554
BROWNIE, IS YOUR MAMA THERE?

01:20:58.621 --> 01:21:01.390
BROWNIE.

01:21:01.457 --> 01:21:05.161
BROWNIE, LET ME TALK TO LEXIE.
PUT YOUR MAMA ON THE PHONE.

01:21:07.630 --> 01:21:11.400
WHY? WHAT'S WRONG?

01:21:11.467 --> 01:21:13.336
I'M COMING.

01:21:22.811 --> 01:21:26.049
[ Dog Barking ]

01:21:27.516 --> 01:21:29.385
LEXIE?

01:21:33.422 --> 01:21:35.291
[ Static ]

01:21:46.869 --> 01:21:48.938
ARE YOU BOTH OKAY?

01:21:54.277 --> 01:21:56.645
YOU STAY HERE, HONEY.
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

01:22:15.731 --> 01:22:17.666
[ Moaning ]

01:22:17.733 --> 01:22:19.568
OH, GOD.

01:22:19.635 --> 01:22:21.470
[ Horn Honks ]

01:22:26.375 --> 01:22:29.745
MOSES, CAN LEXIE KEEP HER THINGS
IN YOUR BARN FOR A WHILE?

01:22:29.812 --> 01:22:32.815
- SURE. HOW COME?
- SHE DOESN'T HAVE ANY MORE
SICK LEAVE,

01:22:32.881 --> 01:22:34.650
AND SHE CAN'T PAY
FOR HER APARTMENT.

01:22:35.918 --> 01:22:38.988
WHERE ARE HER
AND THE KIDS GONNA STAY?

01:22:40.389 --> 01:22:43.226
[ Kids Chattering ]
WE HAD THIS FOR LUNCH.

01:22:43.292 --> 01:22:45.661
WELL, FINISH IT OR YOU'RE
GONNA HAVE IT FOR BREAKFAST.

01:22:48.697 --> 01:22:50.566
NO MORE.

01:22:54.437 --> 01:22:56.305
SORRY, HONEY.

01:22:59.742 --> 01:23:01.577
EAT YOUR FOOD, BROWNIE.

01:23:06.182 --> 01:23:09.385
[ Coughing ]
WANNA EAT?

01:23:48.291 --> 01:23:50.193
LEX.

01:23:51.794 --> 01:23:53.496
YOU ALL RIGHT?

01:24:11.480 --> 01:24:15.484
I WAS SUPPOSED TO WORK
UNTIL 4:00 THAT DAY.

01:24:15.551 --> 01:24:18.987
BUT I DECIDED TO SKIP MY LUNCH
HOUR AND GET OFF AT 3:00...

01:24:19.054 --> 01:24:21.657
'CAUSE ROGER WAS COMING IN
FROM FORT WORTH.

01:24:23.859 --> 01:24:26.562
I WANTED TO TAKE A SHOWER
AND SHAMPOO MY HAIR.

01:24:30.633 --> 01:24:33.802
I PICKED UP THE BABY
AND THE TWINS FROM THE DAY CARE.

01:24:36.038 --> 01:24:41.076
AND WHEN I GOT HOME I WAS
SURPRISED BECAUSE ROGER'S CAR
WAS IN THE DRIVEWAY.

01:24:42.311 --> 01:24:45.013
AND HE SAID HE WOULDN'T BE THERE
UNTIL AFTER 4:00.

01:24:45.080 --> 01:24:48.651
BUT BROWNIE
AND PRALINE WERE HOME,
AND I KNEW THEY'D LET HIM IN.

01:24:51.187 --> 01:24:54.457
WHEN I WENT INSIDE,

01:24:54.523 --> 01:24:57.760
I HEARD A NOISE COMIN'
FROM THE BACK OF THE APARTMENT--

01:24:58.961 --> 01:25:00.829
FROM MY BEDROOM.

01:25:02.865 --> 01:25:06.769
AND I SET DOWN THE BABY,
AND I RAN TO SEE--

01:25:08.404 --> 01:25:10.839
THERE WAS SOMETHIN'
AGAINST THE DOOR.

01:25:11.974 --> 01:25:13.976
I HAD TO PUSH,

01:25:14.042 --> 01:25:16.212
AND IT WAS PRALINE.

01:25:16.279 --> 01:25:19.782
SHE WAS CRUMPLED ON THE FLOOR
COVERIN' HER EYES.

01:25:19.848 --> 01:25:22.385
AND...
[ Crying ]

01:25:22.451 --> 01:25:27.856
ROGER HAD... BROWNIE...
ON THE BED.

01:25:30.193 --> 01:25:32.228
AND HE HAD HIS--

01:25:35.998 --> 01:25:37.866
AND I FLEW AT HIM.

01:25:41.204 --> 01:25:44.440
I WANTED TO KILL HIM
AND I WOULD HAVE.

01:25:44.507 --> 01:25:47.243
I HIT HIM TWICE,
AND THAT'S ALL I REMEMBER.

01:25:50.112 --> 01:25:52.215
YOU KNOW,

01:25:53.216 --> 01:25:55.451
HE WENT AFTER
LITTLE PRALINE FIRST,

01:25:55.518 --> 01:25:58.354
AND SHE THREW UP ON HIM.

01:25:59.688 --> 01:26:02.758
AND THAT'S
WHEN BROWNIE CAME IN.

01:26:10.633 --> 01:26:13.168
HOW DID HE FIND ME,
NOVALEE?

01:26:13.236 --> 01:26:17.139
HOW DO MEN LIKE THAT
FIND MY KIDS?

01:26:17.206 --> 01:26:20.543
HOW'D HE KNOW HE COULD DO
SUCH A THING TO US?

01:26:22.345 --> 01:26:24.547
HE HAD TO BE LOOKIN'.

01:26:24.613 --> 01:26:27.416
HE WAS LOOKIN' FOR WOMEN
LIKE ME...

01:26:27.483 --> 01:26:30.085
WHO ARE ALONE WITH CHILDREN...

01:26:30.152 --> 01:26:32.355
AND WOMEN WHO ARE STUPID.

01:26:33.556 --> 01:26:36.325
AND THEY SAW THROUGH HIM.

01:26:36.392 --> 01:26:38.394
THEY COULD TELL HE WAS EVIL.

01:26:39.862 --> 01:26:42.465
AND ALL I SAW WAS A BUICK.

01:26:47.536 --> 01:26:50.906
OH, GOD.

01:26:50.973 --> 01:26:53.709
WHAT AM I GONNA TELL
MY BABIES?

01:26:53.776 --> 01:26:55.878
WHAT AM I GONNA SAY...

01:26:55.944 --> 01:26:59.815
TO BROWNIE AND PRALINE
WHEN THEY ASK ME WHY
THIS HAPPENED TO THEM?

01:27:01.083 --> 01:27:04.587
[ Sobbing ]
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO SAY,
NOVALEE?

01:27:09.825 --> 01:27:11.960
[ Sighs ]

01:27:12.027 --> 01:27:15.197
YOU TELL THEM--

01:27:15.264 --> 01:27:19.902
YOU TELL THEM THAT OUR--
OUR LIVES CAN CHANGE
WITH EVERY BREATH WE TAKE.

01:27:21.437 --> 01:27:23.406
WE BOTH KNOW THAT.

01:27:24.573 --> 01:27:28.010
AND YOU TELL THEM
TO LET GO OF WHAT'S GONE.

01:27:29.278 --> 01:27:32.615
'CAUSE MEN LIKE ROGER BRISCO
NEVER WIN.

01:27:34.517 --> 01:27:38.987
AND TELL THEM TO HOLD ON
LIKE HELL TO WHAT THEY'VE GOT--

01:27:40.423 --> 01:27:43.926
EACH OTHER AND A MOTHER
WHO WOULD DIE FOR THEM...

01:27:43.992 --> 01:27:46.629
AND ALMOST DID.

01:27:46.695 --> 01:27:50.933
YOU TELL THEM
WE'VE ALL GOT MEANNESS IN US.

01:27:53.469 --> 01:27:56.004
BUT WE'VE GOT GOOD IN US TOO.

01:27:58.607 --> 01:28:01.644
AND THE ONLY THING
WORTH LIVIN' FOR IS THE GOOD.

01:28:01.710 --> 01:28:06.281
AND THAT IS WHY WE'VE GOT
TO MAKE SURE TO PASS IT ON.

01:28:15.991 --> 01:28:17.826
[ Continues Crying ]

01:28:22.365 --> 01:28:24.767
[ Sighs ]

01:28:24.833 --> 01:28:27.803
[ Birds Chirping ]

01:28:29.972 --> 01:28:33.976
FORNEY,
IF YOU FEED A COW CHOCOLATE,
WILL YOU GET CHOCOLATE MILK?

01:28:34.042 --> 01:28:35.411
YEAH.

01:28:35.478 --> 01:28:40.383
AND, IF YOU SPIN
A COW AROUND REAL FAST,
YOU'LL GET WHIPPED CREAM.

01:28:40.449 --> 01:28:43.185
WOW!
YOU KNOW A LOT.

01:28:43.251 --> 01:28:45.421
WELL, I WORK
IN THE LIBRARY.

01:29:24.860 --> 01:29:27.763
I DON'T KNOW HOW YOU KEPT
HER ALIVE THIS LONG, FORNEY.

01:29:29.998 --> 01:29:32.568
YOU'RE WELCOME
TO RIDE ALONG WITH US.

01:30:21.116 --> 01:30:23.018
[ Knock At Door ]

01:30:30.192 --> 01:30:32.194
HOW DID YOU FIND ME?

01:30:32.260 --> 01:30:34.162
SMALL TOWN.

01:30:36.098 --> 01:30:38.634
YOU DIDN'T COME TO THE SERVICE.
I WAS WORRIED.

01:30:38.701 --> 01:30:40.669
I DIDN'T MEAN TO WORRY YOU.

01:30:42.304 --> 01:30:44.807
- CAN I COME IN?
- OKAY.

01:31:03.425 --> 01:31:05.494
YOU ALL RIGHT?

01:31:07.496 --> 01:31:09.865
I COULDN'T STAY AT THE LIBRARY.
I HAD TO--

01:31:09.932 --> 01:31:13.201
I UNDERSTAND.

01:31:13.268 --> 01:31:15.971
I HAVE TO GO AWAY
FOR A WHILE,

01:31:16.038 --> 01:31:18.373
TAKE MARY ELIZABETH
BACK TO MAINE,

01:31:18.440 --> 01:31:20.242
BURY HER IN THE FAMILY PLOT.

01:31:22.377 --> 01:31:24.212
I'M SO SORRY, FORNEY.

01:31:28.416 --> 01:31:30.619
I COULDN'T GO
TO THE SERVICE.

01:31:33.288 --> 01:31:35.891
I HAD FOUR WHITE ROSES.

01:31:37.092 --> 01:31:40.428
AND WHEN I GOT
TO THE SERVICE,
[ Sighs ]

01:31:40.495 --> 01:31:42.965
THEY TURNED BROWN.

01:31:46.535 --> 01:31:49.237
I COULDN'T TAKE HER
BROWN ROSES.

01:31:51.306 --> 01:31:54.176
[ Crying ]

01:32:20.803 --> 01:32:25.407
* I GIVE MY ALL *

01:32:25.473 --> 01:32:29.277
* OR NOT AT ALL *

01:32:31.013 --> 01:32:35.618
* THERE'S NO IN-BETWEEN *

01:32:35.684 --> 01:32:38.887
* I'LL GIVE MY BEST *

01:32:38.954 --> 01:32:43.125
* WON'T SECOND GUESS *

01:32:44.492 --> 01:32:48.764
* THIS FEELING DEEP IN ME *

01:32:48.831 --> 01:32:52.300
* I GIVE MY HEART
GIVE MY SOUL *

01:32:52.367 --> 01:32:57.806
* I WON'T HOLD BACK
I'LL GIVE YOU EVERYTHING **

01:32:57.873 --> 01:33:02.444
[ Whispers ]
NOVALEE.
YEAH?

01:33:02.510 --> 01:33:04.980
I LOVE YOU.

01:33:12.487 --> 01:33:14.456
HE TOLD YOU HE LOVES YOU,

01:33:14.522 --> 01:33:16.491
AND YOU DIDN'T
SAY ANYTHING?

01:33:16.558 --> 01:33:20.562
I'M A DOPE.
I'M SUCH A DOPE.

01:33:20.629 --> 01:33:25.033
BUT I WAS SCARED.
I WAS CONFUSED, AND--
IT'S JUST STRANGE.

01:33:25.100 --> 01:33:27.703
HONEY, DON'T TAKE THIS WRONG,
BUT FORNEY IS STRANGE.

01:33:27.770 --> 01:33:30.372
[ Chuckles ]
SO WHEN'S HE COMIN' BACK?

01:33:30.438 --> 01:33:32.307
[ Car Horn Honks ]

01:33:36.611 --> 01:33:38.380
[ Honking Continues ]

01:33:47.622 --> 01:33:50.492
WHAT WAS THAT ALL ABOUT?
NOTHING.

01:33:50.558 --> 01:33:54.763
NOTHIN'?
WHY WAS ERNIE THE EXTERMINATOR
HONKIN' AT YOU?

01:33:54.830 --> 01:33:59.134
OH. I SAID I'D, UH...
GO OUT WITH HIM.

01:33:59.201 --> 01:34:03.672
YOU TOLD HIM YOU'D WHAT?
I SAID I'D GO OUT
ON A DATE WITH HIM.

01:34:03.739 --> 01:34:07.609
[ Chuckles ]
HOW'D THAT HAPPEN?
TSK.

01:34:07.676 --> 01:34:10.212
WELL, HE'S BROWNIE'S
SOCCER COACH.

01:34:10.278 --> 01:34:14.349
AND HE MAKES HIM LAUGH, WHICH,
LET'S FACE IT, NOBODY DOES.

01:34:14.416 --> 01:34:17.085
AND THAT PSYCHOLOGIST
SAID IT WOULD BE A GOOD IDEA,

01:34:17.152 --> 01:34:19.654
BUT I DON'T KNOW.

01:34:19.722 --> 01:34:23.158
OH, MAN. YOU DON'T THINK
HE'S GONNA WEAR THAT ORANGE
JUMPSUIT ON OUR DATE.

01:34:23.225 --> 01:34:24.993
DO YA?
[ Laughs ]

01:34:30.833 --> 01:34:32.868
[ Bird Squawking ]

01:34:42.377 --> 01:34:46.114
YOU KNOW, MAYBE IT WAS A BAD
IDEA TO TUCK IN THE SHIRTS.

01:34:46.181 --> 01:34:49.818
[ Chattering ]
YEAH. ALL RIGHT. WHOA.

01:34:49.885 --> 01:34:52.620
ISN'T THERE A CHAMPIONSHIP
BANNER OR SOMETHIN'?

01:34:52.687 --> 01:34:57.125
OH, WE'RE NOT THE CHAMPIONS.
WE'RE JUST CELEBRATIN'
WE LIVED THROUGH THE SEASON.

01:34:57.192 --> 01:34:59.527
[ Team Laughing ]
ALL RIGHT.

01:34:59.594 --> 01:35:01.696
WELL, HERE WE GO, THEN.

01:35:01.764 --> 01:35:05.133
SMILE.

01:35:05.200 --> 01:35:07.702
[ Shutter Clicks ]

01:35:07.770 --> 01:35:10.305
NOVALEE, DO YOU KNOW
HOW TO REACH FORNEY?

01:35:10.372 --> 01:35:13.175
IT'S ABOUT SOME LEGAL WORK
INVOLVIN' THE LIBRARY.

01:35:13.241 --> 01:35:15.744
OH, I EXPECT HIM BACK
TODAY OR TOMORROW.

01:35:15.811 --> 01:35:18.981
- FORNEY'S COMIN' BACK?
- SURE.

01:35:19.047 --> 01:35:21.683
WELL, I JUST FIGURED,
WITH MARY ELIZABETH GONE,

01:35:21.750 --> 01:35:24.352
HE'D WANNA PICK UP
WITH HIS LIFE AGAIN...

01:35:24.419 --> 01:35:26.321
OR GO BACK TO COLLEGE.

01:35:26.388 --> 01:35:28.991
HEY, DID YOU KNOW
HIS GREAT GRANDFATHER
WAS GOVERNOR OF MAINE?

01:35:30.458 --> 01:35:32.327
NO.

01:35:32.394 --> 01:35:35.297
WELL, SOMETIMES THINGS WORK OUT
FOR THE BEST.

01:35:35.363 --> 01:35:38.867
NOW HE CAN GET OUT OF HERE
AND HAVE A REAL LIFE.

01:35:40.568 --> 01:35:44.372
ALL RIGHT.
LET'S TAKE THIS PICTURE.
WE'RE ALL STARTIN' TO SMELL.

01:35:44.439 --> 01:35:46.274
[ Phone Ringing ]

01:35:49.611 --> 01:35:51.479
HELLO?

01:35:53.515 --> 01:35:55.350
WHERE ARE YOU?

01:35:56.785 --> 01:35:58.821
WHEN'D YOU GET BACK?

01:35:59.922 --> 01:36:01.857
NO, NO, NO.
I'LL COME OVER.

01:36:01.924 --> 01:36:04.492
I'LL COME THERE.
OKAY? BYE.

01:36:14.269 --> 01:36:16.304
HI.
HEY.

01:36:25.480 --> 01:36:27.315
COME IN.
[ Chuckles ]

01:36:29.151 --> 01:36:32.520
SORRY I CALLED SO LATE.
NO, NO. THAT'S--

01:36:32.587 --> 01:36:34.722
SO HOW WAS YOUR TRIP?
GOOD.

01:36:34.789 --> 01:36:38.226
OKAY.
YOU WANNA SIT DOWN?

01:36:38.293 --> 01:36:40.162
SURE.

01:36:42.364 --> 01:36:45.333
I WAS STARTIN' TO WORRY A LITTLE
WHEN YOU DIDN'T COME BACK.
I THOUGHT--

01:36:45.400 --> 01:36:47.870
OH. I FORGOT
HOW LOVELY IT IS BACK THERE.

01:36:47.936 --> 01:36:51.139
VERY DIFFERENT FROM HERE.
I'LL BET.

01:36:51.206 --> 01:36:54.509
I DROVE OVER TO BOWDEN.
MM-HMM?

01:36:54.576 --> 01:36:57.913
YEAH. I, UH, WAS ONLY
GONNA GO FOR A COUPLE OF HOURS.

01:36:57.980 --> 01:37:02.918
I WIND UP STAYING TWO DAYS.
I SAW A COUPLE OF MY OLD
PROFESSORS.

01:37:02.985 --> 01:37:05.988
I FORGOT WHAT A GREAT LIBRARY
THEY HAVE THERE.

01:37:08.523 --> 01:37:11.293
HAVE THEY HIRED
A NEW LIBRARIAN HERE YET?

01:37:11.359 --> 01:37:15.063
YEAH.
MAYOR ALLBERT'S DAUGHTER.

01:37:15.130 --> 01:37:16.431
OH.
[ Chuckles ]

01:37:18.600 --> 01:37:20.568
WELL.

01:37:20.635 --> 01:37:23.305
OH, WELL. IT'S OKAY.
I WOULDN'T WANT TO
GO BACK THERE ANYWAY.

01:37:25.140 --> 01:37:27.709
I HEAR THEY'RE HIRING
AT THE PLASTICS FACTORY.

01:37:27.775 --> 01:37:30.045
I'LL BET I COULD
GET A JOB THERE.

01:37:31.679 --> 01:37:34.049
ARE YOU OKAY?

01:37:34.116 --> 01:37:36.184
WHAT ABOUT TEACHING?

01:37:36.251 --> 01:37:38.954
YOU SAID ONCE YOU WANTED
TO BE A HISTORY TEACHER.

01:37:39.021 --> 01:37:41.856
OH, THAT WAS A LONG TIME AGO.

01:37:41.924 --> 01:37:46.294
- BUT IF IT'S WHAT YOU WANT, I--
- WHAT I WANT?

01:37:46.361 --> 01:37:51.199
WHAT I WANT
IS TO BE WITH YOU--
TO BE WITH YOU AND AMERICUS.

01:37:52.300 --> 01:37:55.170
I LOVE YOU.
I LOVE YOU SO MUCH.

01:37:55.237 --> 01:37:57.172
WHEN WE WERE HERE TOGETHER--

01:37:57.239 --> 01:37:59.041
THAT MIGHT HAVE BEEN
A MISTAKE.

01:37:59.107 --> 01:38:02.477
- MISTAKE?
- I MEAN--

01:38:02.544 --> 01:38:06.414
ARE YOU SAYING YOU MADE LOVE
TO ME BECAUSE YOU FELT SORRY
FOR ME? IS THAT IT?

01:38:06.481 --> 01:38:10.585
- NO.
- THEN WHAT? IT WAS
A BAD DECISION, AN IMPULSE?

01:38:10.652 --> 01:38:13.355
- FORNEY.
- DO YOU LOVE ME?

01:38:15.023 --> 01:38:19.327
YOU ARE THE BEST FRIEND
I'VE EVER HAD.

01:38:19.394 --> 01:38:23.031
JUST ANSWER ME.
YOU DELIVERED MY BABY.

01:38:23.098 --> 01:38:26.001
DO YOU LOVE ME?

01:38:27.235 --> 01:38:29.137
NO.

01:38:31.339 --> 01:38:36.478
NO, FORNEY,
I DON'T LOVE YOU--
NOT THAT WAY.

01:39:06.975 --> 01:39:09.144
[ Crying ]

01:39:18.153 --> 01:39:20.755
THIS PLACE LOOKS GOOD.

01:39:20.822 --> 01:39:23.758
IT'S NICE AND BRIGHT.

01:39:23.825 --> 01:39:26.394
THE CARPET LOOKS NEW.

01:39:26.461 --> 01:39:29.464
MY KIDS COULD
TURN THIS PLACE INTO A DUMP
BEFORE THE DOOR CLOSES.

01:39:29.531 --> 01:39:32.500
[ Gasps ]
LOOK. YOU CAN SEE THE LIBRARY.

01:39:32.567 --> 01:39:34.802
YEAH.

01:39:34.869 --> 01:39:36.838
YOU EVER HEAR
FROM JOE COLLEGE?

01:39:36.904 --> 01:39:39.074
HE WRITES TO AMERICUS,
SENDS HER BOOKS.

01:39:40.575 --> 01:39:43.045
AT THE END OF EVERY LETTER,
HE WRITES,

01:39:43.111 --> 01:39:46.214
"PLEASE TELL YOUR MOTHER
I EXTEND MY BEST WISHES."

01:39:46.281 --> 01:39:48.816
HOT.
YOU WRITTEN HIM BACK?

01:39:48.883 --> 01:39:52.287
NO. WHAT COULD I SAY TO HIM?

01:39:52.354 --> 01:39:54.689
OH, GOD, THAT
YOU LIED TO HIM FOR ONE.

01:39:54.756 --> 01:39:56.958
THAT YOU LOVE HIM.
THAT YOU MISS HIM.

01:39:57.025 --> 01:39:59.227
THAT THESE HAVE BEEN
THE MOST MISERABLE
THREE MONTHS OF YOUR LIFE...

01:39:59.294 --> 01:40:01.429
AND THAT HE SHOULD COME BACK.

01:40:01.496 --> 01:40:03.498
COME BACK TO WHAT?

01:40:03.565 --> 01:40:05.533
TO A JOB
AT THE PLASTICS FACTORY...

01:40:05.600 --> 01:40:07.802
OR FLIPPIN' BURGERS
AT LITA'S DRIVE-IN?

01:40:07.869 --> 01:40:10.705
OR DRIVIN'
A DELIVERY TRUCK?
WHAT ABOUT WAL-MART?

01:40:10.772 --> 01:40:12.940
NO.
OH, SO IT'S OKAY FOR YOU,

01:40:13.007 --> 01:40:15.310
BUT IT'S NOT GOOD ENOUGH
FOR HIM.

01:40:15.377 --> 01:40:18.680
NO.
NOVALEE, YOU NEVER THOUGHT
YOU DESERVED FORNEY.

01:40:18.746 --> 01:40:21.383
YOU NEVER THOUGHT
YOU WERE GOOD ENOUGH FOR HIM.

01:40:21.449 --> 01:40:23.585
HONEY, I KNOW THAT YOUR MOTHER
WALKED OUT ON YOU...

01:40:23.651 --> 01:40:25.787
AND WHAT THAT BUTTHOLE
WILLY JACK DID,

